organizations.name: Health Service Administration, Student Association
organizations.description: Our Mission: HSASA is an organization comprising students interested in pursuing careers in health care administration. The goal of our organization is to provide networking opportunities for students within the field. We invite professionals from various healthcare organizations to talk to our members about their careers as well as other pertinent healthcare topics. Also, we participate in numerous events throughout the year including socials, intramural sports, philanthropic events, and fundraisers.  Any student, regardless of major or academic level, currently enrolled in classes at UCF may join our organization. Please check the "Events" tab on the left-hand side to RSVP or to find out more information about upcoming philanthropic events and tour dates! Spaces are limited so please make sure to RSVP in advance. For further information, contact hsasa@ucf.edu. To directly contact our president, Derric Esquivel, send an e-mail to de667145@ucf.edu.

organizations.name: Zeta Tau Alpha Fraternity
organizations.description: Seek the Noblest!

organizations.name: Knights of Fiber Arts
organizations.description: We are a club that allows students interested in hobbies under the umbrella of fiber arts (i.e. knitting, crocheting, sewing, etc.) to meet and socialize with other students with similar hobbies. Through weekly, casual meetings, we get to know each other, form friendships, and work on our personal projects! We may occasionally have meetings at different locations, but often enjoy picnics!

organizations.name: The Cypress Dome Society
organizations.description: The Cypress Dome Society is the University of Central Florida's literary organization staffed by undergraduate students. Named after a feature of the landscape on the UCF campus, we are dedicated to fostering the literary arts and promoting a sense of community among writers and artists through events and our annual publication, The Cypress Dome, UCF's undergraduate literary journal.  Founded in 1989, The Cypress Dome received the Associated Writing Programs Directors' Award for exceptional content in 1995. It is edited, designed, and produced by a selected editorial team of The Cypress Dome Society students as part of a year-long internship. Poetry, fiction, creative nonfiction, flash fiction/nonfiction, graphic narratives, and visual art may be submitted in the fall term, according to submission guidelines distributed each fall, to be considered for publication in the annual issue published each spring. Our events, such as our monthly Open Mic sessions, and our publication seek to cultivate creativity and diversity and are open to both graduate and undergraduate students.  For more information on how to get involved in The Cypress Dome Society, contact us or join our Discord ( https://discord.gg/MSAhPUgAyx ) If you are interested in submitting your work for publication in The Cypress Dome , please visit our website: https://cah.ucf.edu/cypressdome/ .

organizations.name: Student Engagement (UCF Downtown and Valencia College Downtown Campus)
organizations.description: This functional area of UCF Downtown and Valencia College Downtown campus serves as a conduit for student to participate in co-curricular activities, campus advocacy, community engagement, and social justice.   If you would like to reserve our Student Success and Engagement Lobby located on the 2nd floor of Union West, please email studentengagement@ucf.edu

organizations.name: Orientation Team
organizations.description: Orientation Leaders (OLs) serve as critical members of the First Year Experience (FYE) team and are current undergraduate students who are dedicated to UCF and seeking to serve on a team of role models for all UCF students. We aren't going to lie: this position is demanding. But when done well, we believe it's more rewarding than any other job on campus! You and your teammates get to shape the experiences and journey of thousands of new students and families coming into UCF! You become a first friend, a mentor, resource, and source of knowledge and inspiration to new Knights! Apply by Wednesday, October 5, 2022. Application available Monday, August 22, 2022.

organizations.name: LEAD Scholars Academy
organizations.description: Welcome to the LEAD Scholars Academy. This office provides students with various opportunities to learn more about themselves, develop new leadership skills, and become student leaders through programs and events, including Campus-wide Leadership Workshops, Leadership Retreats, and Leadership Conferences.

organizations.name: Botanical Society at the University of Central Florida
organizations.description: The mission of Botanical Society of America is to create a community for students interested in botanical sciences. By forming a community of plant science students with the Botanical Society of America we will be able to offer professional development opportunities and help link students to internships and jobs.    General Body Meetings on the last Wednesday of every month.  Join our Discord for up to date club info! (https://discord.gg/fErqUW4WJ4)

organizations.name: Video Game Music Ensemble @UCF
organizations.description: Founded in 2023, the Video Game Music Ensemble @UCF is a student-led ensemble open to all current UCF students. They play music from a wide variety of video games, old and new. The ensemble aims to bring students together with their love of music from video games. If you are interested in joining please fill out the sign-up form. Sign-up on our Linktree See our most recent concert here

organizations.name: National Association of Hispanic Journalists
organizations.description: The National Association of Hispanic Journalists (NAHJ) at UCF is  dedicated to the recognition and professional advancement of hispanic students in journalism and other areas in the media. NAHJ is an educational and charitable association, which offers scholarships, conferences and other opportunities. Here at UCF, we promote internships and create a student-produced webcast each semester.  Any students who are interested in diversity and inclusion in the media are welcome to join our club, regardless of major or background.

organizations.name: A Heartfulness Meditation Experience
organizations.description: Our objective is to equip UCF students with a set of inner practices for personality development and self growth. We offer meditation and relaxation training to the entire UCF community with support from certified Heartfulness Trainers. Heartfulness: Living by the Heart By tuning into our hearts, we learn to be centered in our highest selves. We can learn to strengthen that connection and cultivate an inner knowing that wisely directs and guides our lives. With practice, we can grow to face the challenges of life with courage and acceptance. If we live by the heart, we can become what we're meant to be. Explore and experience. Feel the lightness and joy of your true nature. Heartfulness meditation is simply taking the time every day to tune into that internal presence. In a short while, you'll learn to remain connected to that gentle support throughout the day. Heartfulness meditation can students to learn how to: 1. Relax for physical well-being 2. Deepen your meditation 3. Simplify thoughts 4. Unwind the mind 5. Let go of stress, rejuvenate 6. Observe your deepest feelings 7. Make wise life choices 8. Find inner strength 9. Develop confidence and balance 10. Nurture relationships 11. Find joy within

organizations.name: Active Minds
organizations.description: Active Minds UCF is a chapter of the nation's leading  nonprofit organization  dedicated to helping young people be open about mental health. Our mission is to break the stigma surrounding mental health and let people know it's okay to need help! We host biweekly hybrid GBMs about different topics related to mental health and aim to create a supportive peer-led community on campus. Fall Membership Applications are now open! To become a member: 1. Select "Join" on KnightConnect 2. Complete and submit a Membership Application Form 3. Join our Discord   Fall Membership Application closes on 9/29/25 at 11:59 PM

organizations.name: Society For Biomaterials
organizations.description: The goals of SFB at UCF shall be to identify students interested in biomaterials, to generate student interest and interaction in biomaterials, and to aid the efficacy of students seeking research, education, and professional development opportunities.

organizations.name: The Bahamian Student Association
organizations.description: The Bahamian Student Association (BAHSA) at the University of Central Florida is a cultural and community-based organization dedicated to celebrating and promoting Bahamian heritage on campus. Our mission is to create a supportive environment for Bahamian and non-Bahamian students alike by fostering unity, cultural pride, and academic success.

organizations.name: President's Leadership Council
organizations.description: President's Leadership Council (PLC) at the University of Central Florida (UCF)  is a select group of 35 student ambassadors who demonstrate leadership, service, scholarship and academic excellence. Council members serve the university in a variety of capacities, including hosting special guests on and off campus and at various presidential events, such as appreciation receptions, university Board of Trustees' and state Board of Governors' functions, and the President's Suite at campus sporting events.  The PLC also serves as an extension of the presidency, allowing students to take an active advisory and advocacy role on campus.

organizations.name: Neptune Community
organizations.description: To provide a residence life program that encourages a positive living and learning environment, supportive of students development in the college community by providing quality opportunities and connections for academic and personal growth.

organizations.name: Biomedical Sciences Graduate Student Association
organizations.description: The goals of BSGSA include: 1. Provide a forum for discussion of issues relevant to graduate students within the Burnett School of Biomedical Science and others in the university community. 2. Organize, promote and conduct activities beneficial to Biomedical Sciences graduate students and enhance their graduate education at the University of Central Florida.

organizations.name: Raas Rampage
organizations.description: Raas Rampage supports vital philanthropic causes to the South Asian community to preserve South Asian traditions in the Orlando area. Rampage also celebrates the Raas-Garba tradition by sharing the South Asian culture with the UCF and Orlando community.

organizations.name: Association of Latino Professionals For America
organizations.description: At ALPFA UCF, success isn't just a goal; it's a reality we cultivate for our members. With a track record of guiding students toward their career aspirations and seamlessly integrating them into prestigious Fortune 500 firms, ALPFA UCF stands as a beacon of achievement and opportunity. What sets us apart? We boast the distinction of being one of the largest, most diverse, and incredibly successful ALPFA student chapters nationwide. Our success is not by chance but by design, fueled by the unwavering mentality and work ethic of our exceptional members. As we champion each member's journey, our corporate partners play a pivotal role in fostering an environment of continuous growth. Imagine being part of a network that spans over 72,000 members nationally. ALPFA's reach goes beyond the campus, connecting you to a vast pool of opportunities and like-minded individuals passionate about success in the world of finance and business. We take pride in being more than a student organization; we are a community that thrives on collaboration, diversity, and collective achievement. Our members don't just join ALPFA; they join a family committed to empowering each other and making a lasting impact in their chosen fields. Visit our social media pages below to catch a glimpse of the ALPFA UCF experience or explore our website for a comprehensive view of how we can elevate your academic and professional pursuits. üåê [ALPFA UCF Website ] üì∑ [ Instagram ] üë• [ LinkedIn ] Join ALPFA UCF and unlock the doors to a world of possibilities, mentorship, and success. Your journey to excellence starts here.

organizations.name: Knights Powerlifting
organizations.description: Knights powerlifting works to support strength athletes. Powerlifting entails the three big lifts: squat bench and deadlift. We welcome any student that loves fitness, want more information on powerlifting, or are looking for a supportive group of people that share a passion and love for strength training.

organizations.name: Bhakti Yoga Club
organizations.description: The Bhakti Yoga Club is dedicated to creating a safe space where we are all welcome to come and free the mind from the stresses of daily life and make a deeper connection with yourself through meditation, music, books, and food.   For updates about our club just check out our linktree :) https://linktr.ee/ucfbhaktiyogaclub check out @bhaktihouseorlando on insta for updates and to get in contact with us

organizations.name: The Navigators
organizations.description: The Navigators is a Christian campus ministry that seeks to make Jesus known and help others do the same. Our ministry has a strong focus on discipleship, doing life together as a community. We also provide spaces for fellowship and Bible study. You can come join us every Thursday night at 8 on campus!

organizations.name: The Fencing Knights @ UCF
organizations.description: The Fencing Knights at UCF is open to students of all skill levels who want to learn or practice the sport of fencing. We offer lessons from our coach with 40+ years of experience and compete in tournaments in and around the state of Florida. For those new to the sport, we provide all the necessary equipment and can teach you everything you need to know to start fencing like a pro! organizations.name: Kappa Sigma Fraternity
organizations.description: Kappa Sigma is committed to the Four Pillars: Fellowship, Leadership, Scholarship, and Service. As a values-based fraternity, it firmly opposes hazing and prioritizes a positive college experience through progressive membership development and education. This focus on personal growth and meaningful relationships empowers members to become impactful leaders and active community contributors, fostering lifelong friendships and essential skills that last beyond their college years.

organizations.name: Dabke Student Organization
organizations.description: The Dabke Student Organization is to bring the Arab culture closer and help students learn the traditional dances of their heritage. We strive to teach others also about our culture and the fun we have.

Outlanders at UCF
organizations.description: Welcome!   Hello and welcome to Outlanders at UCF! We are a camping and general outdoorsmanship club here at the University of Central Florida. We offer students the opportunity to experience the outdoors in a fun and stress-free way. It is our goal to foster a community of outdoor enthusiasts to promote interpersonal connections, outdoorsmanship, and environmental awareness. Trips are cheap and we offer free equipment rentals!   Want to learn more about us? Register with us here on KnightConnect and then join our Discord linked on our instagram! organizations.name: Diversified Greek Council
organizations.description: On behalf of the Diversified Greek Council (DGC) and Greek Community, we would like to congratulate you and welcome you to the University of Central Florida! Your journey is just beginning and there is so much our university offers and one of the greatest opportunities is to become members of the Greek Community. We are excited to celebrate our 25 years with you all! In the spring of 1999, DGC was created and was established as a council for culturally diverse Greek letter organizations. We pride on being an inclusive council whose mission is to promote scholastic excellence, cultural awareness, and community engagement. Currently we are home to nine different sororities and fraternities, each promoting diversity and spreading cultural awareness! Although DGC does not have a formal recruitment period, DGC hosts an informational event called ‚ÄúCultural Fair‚Äù at the beginning of Fall & Spring semester that allows students to meet our community, learn more about our chapters and values. We also host the "DGC Yardshow" towards the end of the semester where you can witness our traditions such as saluting, stepping and strolling. We know you‚Äôll find the home you‚Äôre looking for and we wish you a great year. Check out our Instagram @ dgcucf  for more information on our chapters and if you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us at dgc@ucf.edu ! We can‚Äôt wait to meet you and the legacy you‚Äôll make here.

organizations.name: National Society of Leadership and Success
organizations.description: The NSLS is the largest leadership honor society in the United States. Our NSLS chapter at University of Central Florida was started in 2003. Our local chapter is part of the national organization with 700+ chapters and over 1.4 million members. Students are selected based on exemplary academic achievement. Our members are given access to: · More than $400,000 in scholarships. · An exclusive NSLS job board. · A personalized letter of recommendation. The NSLS leadership program teaches the interpersonal skills that employers seek to give you an edge in the job market. Hear directly from current members as they share how their experience has changed their life. If you become a member, some of the other benefits are: · Learn from exceptional leaders like former presidents George Bush and Barack Obama during exclusive Speaker Broadcasts. · Meet new friends and make lifelong connections (on-campus and virtually). · Overcome challenges with success coaches shortcutting your way to success. · Access to private networking events. Visit the NSLS website to learn more about and accept your nomination at www.nsls.org Frequently Asked Questions: Some of the common questions we receive are listed below. If you have any other questions, visit nsls.org to chat with a team member or email help@nsls.org . What do I have to do to become inducted? Our five-step program takes approximately 10 hours over the course of the semester at your pace. Is this recognized on campus? We are a Registered Student Organization (RSO). There are also more than 1.4 million members nationwide. I am interested in joining but I haven't been invited what do I do? Feel free to fill out the nomination for at https://members.nsls.org/nomination/application

organizations.name: Young Poets' Society
organizations.description: Established 2022, the Young Poets' Society (YPS) was created to foster the skills of poets, be it new or old. The club holds monthly meetings where members are encouraged to write and share poems in an inclusive and supportive environment. The club's social media channels allow prospective and returning members to keep up with meeting times, as well as club-sponsored events, such as performance opportunities, outings, and more. All are welcome at our socials and open mics. For any questions, feel free to email us at ypsucf@gmail.com or DM an officer on our Discord !

organizations.name: Pre-Optometry Association
organizations.description: The mission of the Pre-Optometry Association (POA) is to equip students with the knowledge and resources needed to pursue a career in optometry. Through exposure to the application process, the Optometry Admission Test (OAT), insights from practicing optometrists, and volunteer opportunities, POA supports students on their path to optometry school. This club provides a welcoming environment for like-minded students who want to help others see the world in perfect clarity.   The best way to keep up to date with our events is to follow us on Instagram @UCF_PREOPTOMETRY

organizations.name: Happiest Club on Earth at Orlando
organizations.description: The Happiest Club on Earth at Orlando (HCOE) is a social club at the University of Central Florida's main campus in Orlando. HCOE offers a safe space to share the magic of Disney and meet friends with similar interests. We host various club adventures, including themed socials, trips around Disney property, and much more! HCOE welcomes everyone with open arms: casual enjoyers and Disney adults alike! Membership is open to every UCF student, with or without annual passes to Walt Disney World.

organizations.name: Delta Phi Lambda Sorority, Inc
organizations.description: Delta Phi Lambda Sorority, Inc. is a 501(c)(7) non-profit organization that advocates Asian awareness and empowers women to lead through values-based programs and everlasting sisterhood. Delta Phi Lambda's national philanthropy is osteoporosis education and prevention, emphasizing the importance of promoting healthy lifestyles and behavior in young women. Founded in 1998, Delta Phi Lambda Sorority, Inc. has grown to 25 undergraduate chapters in 16 states spanning the Southeast, Midwest, and the Northeast.

organizations.name: Baja International
organizations.description: Baja International focuses on developing the best professionals for engineering-related industries through a large-scale project that incorporates all aspects of engineering, business, and project management. The mission of Knights Racing Baja SAE is to represent UCF through participation in Baja SAE's collegiate design series competitions and to provide UCF students with hands-on engineering experience and the opportunity to apply their theoretical knowledge. While we compete in competitions hosted by the Society of Automotive Engineers, we are not exclusive to engineering majors. UCF students of all majors, regardless of background, are welcome and invited to join Baja.

organizations.name: Marine Biology Education and Awareness Club
organizations.description: MBEAC is a club that works to educate students, no matter their major or background, on the world of marine biology. Our main goal is to emphasize that learning about marine biology can and should be exciting and interactive, through fun social events, group study halls, field trips, casual volunteer opportunities, and body meetings. We also offer career outreach opportunities to members, like guest speaker visits at our body meetings, grad school preparation workshops, class schedule planning discussions, and an opportunities board in our Discord server. Check out the links below to get involved. We hope you'll join us! linktr.ee/marinebioucf

organizations.name: Softball Club @ UCF
organizations.description: Mission Statement: Provide a competitive and culturally diverse environment for those students who wish to play softball at the college level.

organizations.name: Society of Asian Scientists and Engineers
organizations.description: SASE is dedicated to the advancement of Asian heritage scientists and engineers in education and employment so that they can achieve their full career potential. SASE's mission is to prepare Asian heritage scientists and engineers for success in the global business world, celebrate diversity on campuses and in the workplace, and provide opportunities for members to make contributions to their local communities. In addition to SASE National's mission, the University of Central Florida chapter seeks to connect individuals in a way that benefits both their professional and personal lives. SASE membership is open to everyone regardless of background and major.    If you are interested in joining, here is our linktr.ee!  https://linktr.ee/saseucf

organizations.name: Swim Club at UCF
organizations.description: From beginner level to advanced levels, swimmers can join for fun and even for a competition. There are travel meets where the team is able to bond and go to team dinners and explore the area after the meets as well as in state meets. Come out and join us any semester, check the Instagram for any announcements (https://www.instagram.com/ucfknightsswimming?igsh=NTc4MTIwNjQ2YQ%3D%3D)

organizations.name: Amateur Radio Club at UCF
organizations.description: The Amateur Radio Club at UCF strives to create an environment where anyone can learn the many aspects of amateur radio. Whether that will be in electronics (including AC and DC circuitry), communications, or even using the radio, we have room for anyone wanting to explore these interests and broaden their horizons in the art of amateur radio. Our Linktree, which contains links to our Discord, wiki, and other resources: https://linktr.ee/k4ucf If you use your @ucf.edu address when emailing us, you will get a faster response.

organizations.name: Health Occupations Students of America UCF (HOSA UCF)
organizations.description: The mission of HOSA is to empower aspiring future health professionals by creating opportunities for students to develop passion in helping all people through leadership, scholarship, community partnership, individual improvement, and collaboration.

organizations.name: Shantymen of the Knight
organizations.description: Join the Discord Server to Get Involved!

organizations.name: Kappa Pi International Honorary Art Fraternity
organizations.description: Mission The mission of this society will be to form bodies of representative students who will, by their influence and artistic interests, uphold the highest ideals of a liberal education; to provide a means whereby students with artistic commitment meet for the purpose of informal study and communications; to raise the standards of productive artistic work among the students in the colleges and universities; to furnish the highest reward for conscientious effort in furthering the best interest of art in the broadest sense of the term, by election to membership in the society, based upon such meritorious work. Goal Our goal is to offer art students a society of like minded individuals in which success, talent, creativity and scholarship can be nurtured and grown. A place where students with a similar passion for the visual arts can enjoy the excursions, lectures, exhibitions and companionship that comes from being part of a group of purpose driven peers.

organizations.name: Student Financial Planning Association
organizations.description: The mission of SFPA is to assist and connect the students of UCF with the industry of Financial Planning through educational seminars as well as networking events with Certified Financial Planners. Our goal is a create a network of students who are motivated and passionate about the financial planning process and interested in connecting with likeminded members. Central Florida has a plethora of excellent wealth management firms who are eager to find interns and employees, our organization is looking to bring the spotlight to UCF.

organizations.name: Master of Social Work Student Association
organizations.description: Thank you for your interest in the Master of Social Work Student Association (MSWSA) at UCF! The goals of our organization is to create a supportive environment where MSW students can connect with one another, practice self-care, network and engage in professional growth opportunities through MSWSA-sponsored meetings and events.   You must be an actively enrolled student in UCF's Master of Social Work program to apply.   Membership includes a t-shirt and participation in MSWSA-sponsored events.    Apply to become a member here:  MSWSA Application   The one-time membership fee is $10. Cash, Check, Money order or Venmo @ucfmswsa payments can be given to our MSWSA Advisor, Mrs. Mays. Please email Jessica.Mays@ucf.edu to coordinate drop-off.    To receive your t-shirt and participate in events, you must pay your $10 membership fee  AND  accept your Knights Connect invitation that will be sent to your UCF email.    All MSWSA communications will be sent to your UCF email, as well as Discord. To stay updated, follow us on Instagram: @mswsa.ucf and please join the Discord here: https://discord.gg/5z8bjHRtGW   If you have any questions or concerns, please contact MSWSA@ucf.edu. Thank you!

organizations.name: Lambda Alpha Epsilon Pre-Professional Criminal Justice Fraternity
organizations.description: Lambda Alpha Epsilon is a co-ed pre-professional fraternity established in 1937. UCF's Delta Zeta Omega chapter at was founded in 1992. LAE alumni work throughout the country in a wide array of criminal justice agencies, including teaching CJ at the collegiate level. As a pre-professional fraternity, LAE prides itself in offering its members networking and community opportunities, fun social events, Bigs and Littles, and the opportunity to create friendships with individuals that pride themselves in the same interests: Public Service!           Every other week, LAE brings in a guest speaker, allowing its members to bond as a family and learn more about the plenitude of pathways one can take in CJ. Guest speakers in the past have included, but are not limited to, Orange County Sheriff's Office, FBI Terrorism Task Force, DEA, Orange County Corrections, Miami Beach Police Department, Victim Services, FDLE, and much more.           In the past, LAE has put together SWAT roundup, FBI hazmat training, and our annual Public Service Conference. These are just a few of the opportunities LAE prides itself in sharing with its members, all in an effort to help them feel more confident about their career choices post-graduation.           LAE is also very involved in its community with organizations such as Harbor House, Second Harvest, and Clean the World. We also host an annual Domestic Violence Awareness Charity Auction in October. Though a career-based fraternity, LAE encourages community and fellowship with its members by organizing events such as icebreakers, bowling nights, group workouts (possibly intramural sports), volunteer events, and Fall/Spring Formals.           Requirements: Members must maintain a 2.0 cumulative GPA, complete 10 hours of community service every semester, attend socials, partake in fundraisers, professional, and academic events, pay a semester fee, and meet bi-weekly 6:00 PM in our assigned location. All of this must be done to stay in Good-Standing. For more information and further updates, follow our Instagram @ucflae. Please note that dues and contracts must be turned in before membership will be approved on KnightConnect.

organizations.name: Student Accounting Society
organizations.description: The Student Accounting Society is a professional organization, established in 1974, which unites students preparing for a career in the accounting field. Joining SAS is the ideal way to make connections with professionals who can be key to your career growth and development while also building a network of peers who will support you in your academic and professional successes. Please see our website for additional information on joining @ sasucf.org ! We recruit every Fall and Spring! Recruitment begins at the beginning of every semester, so be sure to visit our website for any updates! Email any questions to ucfsas@gmail.com

organizations.name: Knights Cheer
organizations.description: In Knights Cheer Club (KCC) our goal is to allow student members to maintain and improve their cheerleading ability at the collegiate level. We encompass several competitive teams at various skill levels to ensure the inclusion of all members. We also stress the importance of not only the physical aspects of cheerleading but also the fundamentals of what it means to be a leader, both on and off the mat. We pride ourselves on exemplifying the core values of being a UCF Knight.

organizations.name: Children Beyond Our Borders
organizations.description: Our mission is to provide opportunities for children and youth affected by armed conflict and social injustice to find peace, prosperity and well-being through education and empowerment. Every child, regardless of social status, race or gender, deserves a proper education. Every child deserves to live a stable life without barriers and without fear. Every child deserves to dream ‚Äì and to dream big. Every child deserves a brighter future ‚Äì a future that breaks boundaries and goes beyond borders. organizations.name: Student Government Executive Branch
organizations.description: We Moved! Student Government is now located on the Third Floor of the Student Union in Suite 346!!!   UCF Student Government is a representative body modeled after the United States government. Through its three branches, Executive , Legislative , and Judicial , Student Government aims to represent student issues and concerns at all levels of University decision making. Through a $20.4 million dollar budget acquired from student fees, SG maintains hundreds of student jobs, oversees two facilities (Student Union and Rec & Wellness Center), and is constantly creating new services and initiatives aiming to make campus life better for all UCF Knights. The Executive Branch (or Cabinet) is composed of  student leaders appointed by the Student Body President each year. Our cabinet consists of a diverse group of students who share a passion for helping their university grow and making sure their peers receive the best education possible. We sit on over thirty-five different University Councils where we represent the average student and ensure that the student voice is heard loud and clear. The Executive Branch is also responsible for the development and maintenance of many significant student programs and services such as the Safe Ride Program, the Recreation & Wellness Center , Universal Knights, town hall meetings, educational programs, diversity education events, and many others

organizations.name: Alpha Phi Sigma Criminal Justice Honor Society
organizations.description: Alpha Phi Sigma  recognizes the academic excellence of Undergraduate and Graduate Criminal Justice students.  The Goals of Alpha Phi Sigma are to honor and promote academic excellence, community service, educational leadership, and unity.  Alpha Phi Sigma is the only Criminal Justice Honor Society certified by The Association of College Honor Societies and affiliated with The Academy of Criminal Justice Sciences. Baccalaureate students shall be enrolled at the time of application in the institution represented by the chapter, have declared a major, minor, or equivalent in criminal justice or a related field, have completed three full-time semesters or its equivalent, have a minimum GPA of 3.2 on a 4.0 scale, with a minimum GPA of 3.2 in courses in criminal justice related fields and rank in the top 35% of their class. A minimum of four courses of the above coursework shall be in the criminal justice field. Masters students shall be enrolled at the time of application in a Master's program in the Criminal Justice field in the institution represented by the chapter, have completed four courses, and have a minimum GPA of 3.4 on a 4.0 scale. Up to three undergraduate courses in Criminal Justice may be used to satisfy the four-course requirement. These courses must equate to a 3.4 GPA or higher, and the cumulative undergraduate degree program GPA must be a 3.2 or higher. In addition, all master's level coursework must equate to a 3.4 GPA or higher at the institution in which the student is enrolled. Doctoral students shall be enrolled at the time of application in a Ph.D. program in the Criminal Justice field in the institution represented by the chapter, have completed four courses, and have a minimum GPA of 3.6 on a 4.0 scale. Up to three master's courses in Criminal Justice may be used to satisfy the four-course requirement. These courses must equate to a 3.6 GPA or higher, and the cumulative Master's degree program GPA must be a 3.4 or higher. In addition, all Ph.D. level coursework must equate to a 3.6 GPA or higher at the institution in which the student is enrolled. Completed applications must be submitted to the chapter advisor for verification and signature. Applications are due by October 1 for Fall admission and Feb 1 for Spring admission.

organizations.description: Veterans Medical Outreach aspires to close the gap between the homeless veteran community and the healthcare system. organizations.name: Knights of the Paw
organizations.description: Knights of the Paw is UCF's official student club for fans of anthropomorphic animals in art and media, also known as 'furries'.   Post-con depression? At Knights of the Paw ("KniP" for short), we aim to hold events that share the joy of the furry fandom and do lots of opportunities for hangouts on/outside of campus. Overall, we are a group that will make you feel welcomed and give you a chance to feel more included here at UCF!  Our core values are community , creativity , and philanthropy : ü¶ä Community ü¶ä We strive to enrich the lives of our members by offering them a place to make friends through a common hobby and offering social activities and workshops. We host many events - from casual food meetups to full on fursuiting events! Our members have a wide range of interests and majors to connect beyond furry. Our group is also largely LGBTQ+ and so this is a very welcome, open, and safe environment for all people from all walks of life! üê≤ Creativity üê≤ One of the biggest subgroups in the furry fandom are artists! Costumers, crafters, writers, musicians, and more make our hobby what it is. We encourage students to pursue their creative interests and celebrate their unique selves with art jams and activities! üêØ Philanthropy üêØ   Furries actively seek to do good not only for our members but for our local community and beyond! We in KniP focus on charitable work through volunteering and fundraising for organizations such as the Pet Alliance of Greater Orlando and more.   Interested? Feel free to join our club as a member and get into contact with one of our officers! We are open to everyone - including non-furries - and wish to foster better understanding behind the fandom, as well as spark inspiration to our furry members and beyond!   (NOTE: Once signed up, PLEASE check your UCF email for further instructions to access our online platforms.)

organizations.name: Progressive Black Men, Incorporated
organizations.description: Progressive Black Men, Inc. aims to eradicate negative stereotypes placed on those of African descent through Academic Excellence , Communal Support , and the Fellowship of Brothers .   Our vision is to reconstruct and redefine the image of the Black male and uplift people of African American through: Brotherhood , Community Service , Humanitarian Aid , and the Development of High Standards of Personal Integrity and Moral Character .   PBM was founded on the campus of Florida State University on November 27th, 1989 .   The UCF Chapter, nicknamed " Famous ", was chartered on November 9th, 2014. Miss Progressive Black Men Scholarship Pageant , Women Appreciation Night , and Walk a Mile in Her Shoes are just a few of the notable events held on campus. organizations.name: Society of Environmental Engineers
organizations.description: The Society of Environmental Engineers is a club where students can meet, network, and work alongside other students and Environmental Engineering professionals, gaining valuable knowledge of the field. Though it is primarily aimed at those pursuing a degree in Environmental Engineering, the club is open to and welcomes anyone interested in the subject.  The club provides several exciting opportunities to learn and gain a deeper understanding of the profession outside the classroom. Guest lecturers come from all disciplines of Environmental Engineering, including wastewater control, air pollution control, and more. These professionals share insights into their careers, life after college, and offer tips on how to be successful in the field.  In addition to guest lectures, we have attended a variety of specific tours that provide valuable real-world exposure. These include energy plant tours, landfill tours, water treatment plant tours, and wastewater treatment plant tours. These tours give students a firsthand look at the operations and challenges within different sectors of Environmental Engineering.  SEE also holds several volunteering events throughout the year, giving students a chance to get outdoors and make an impact in local communities. Our involvement with FWEA and AWWA has included beach and river cleanups. In previous years, we have attended specific tours such as plant tours and industry conferences, providing valuable real-world exposure.    There are several chances to make a difference throughout the year. Please come out to one of our meetings or events and see what the club is all about!  Join our Discord and access our other platforms here ! SEE also represents FWEA and A&WMA here at UCF! FWEA - Florida Water Environment Association -  https://www.fwea.org/ A&WMA - Air & Waste Management Association -  https://www.awma.org/

To spread awareness of relevant issues and current events that may impact such marginalized communities. To raise public awareness of the necessity of positive youth engagement. To provide young people with personal and leadership development training.

Begin your journey by joining one of our Agencies or over 670+ Registered Student Organizations across all UCF Campuses. organizations.name: Phi Eta Sigma National Honor Society
organizations.shortName: Phi Eta Sigma National Honor Society
organizations.description: The mission of Phi Eta Sigma is to not only reward academic excellence, but to encourage students to continue to excel in their scholastic endeavors. Joining Phi Eta Sigma means becoming a part of a  nationwide community  that dedicated to achieving excellence and elevating the college experience. By becoming a member of Phi Eta Sigma, students have access to  exclusive  scholarships opportunities and programs that are specifically designed to  enhance  their academic and professional development. Phi Eta Sigma provides more than $400,000 in local and national scholarships through our Founders Fund and chapter resources. Phi Eta Sigma prides ourselves in awarding scholarships to students who have demonstrated leadership, service, academic excellence, and a commitment and involvement within Phi Eta Sigma. In Phi Eta Sigma, we believe in providing opportunities for our students to grow holistically through the development of their mind, health, and character. These three values provide the foundational component for all Phi Eta Sigma programming at the National and Regional levels. We are a network of students, alumni, and faculty/staff who are dedicated to an elevated college experience for themselves and others. Our society offers opportunities for networking, engagement, and meaningful connections on our campus and throughout the nation. As a member, you will have exclusive access to events, and resources that will assist you in building your community within Phi Eta Sigma.

organizations.name: Pre-Professional Medical Society
organizations.description: The Pre-Professional Medical Society (PPMS) is a unique organization that unites pre-professional students with diverse career aspirations based on their many common interests. PPMS provides its members with a variety of speakers from interrelated professions, giving members an inside look at their future careers. Our members gain an edge over competing professional school applicants by becoming knowledgeable of admission processes as well as current issues in healthcare. Members are supplied with ample opportunity to help those in need by volunteering in our local community. PPMS creates a supportive environment for our members through various social events, allowing our members to build trusting relationships with their peers. Our ultimate goal is to see that each member is accepted into the professional school of their dreams.     Go to our website for all important information! Website: https://ucfppms.wixsite.com/ppmsucf TikTok: @ucf.ppms Facebook: facebook.com/ucfppms Instagram: instagram.com/ucfppms Twitter: twitter.com/ucfppms General Email: ucfppms@gmail.com GroupMe: https://groupme.com/join_group/89111943/XsESLra5   PPMS Executive Board 2025-2026 PRESIDENT- Valerie Block PresidentPPMS@gmail.com VICE PRESIDENT-  Tai Powell VicePresidentPPMS@gmail.com P.S.I. organizations.name: Apollo Community
organizations.description: The mission of the Department of Housing and Residence Life is to provide students living in university housing with a safe and secure environment that is conducive to academic and personal achievement.

organizations.name: Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Inc.
organizations.description: Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Incorporated was the first Black Greek Letter organization established for collegiate black men. It was founded by 7 young men on the prodominantly white campus of Cornell University in 1906. Open to men of all diversities, Alpha Phi Alpha has become a pillar worldwide with prominent members such as Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr., Cornell West, Hill Harper Frederick Douglas, Olympian Jesse Owens, Duke Ellington, and many more.

organizations.name: National Black Law Student Association
organizations.description: UCF's chapter of the National Black Law Student's Association(NBLSA)  is a nationally recognized pre-law organization that is geared towards developing successful legal professionals who are driven and enthusiastic to bring about meaningful change in our communities and throughout the globe. We take great pride in helping all members get a step closer to their fulfilling careers within the legal field.    NBLSA strives to provide academic enrichment and professional development within a culturally diverse atmosphere. We discuss a variety of social issues, business etiquette, resume and personal statement critique as well as law school and LSAT success strategies.   We host an array of professionals within the legal field and give plenty of networking opportunities including highly respected lawyers, judges, law students and deans and other law school and LSAT representatives. We take great pride in our organization and would love to share that with you.

organizations.name: Club Kreyol
organizations.description: The mission of Club Kreyol is to be missionaries of the Creole culture by bringing awareness, drawing interest, and illustrating its diversity to UCF and the surrounding community. Club Kreyol (CK ) represents nine Creole-speaking nations (Haiti, St Lucia, Martinique, Guadeloupe, Dominica, Mauritius, Reunion Island, Seychelles and French Guiana) and works to preserve Creole culture in this and future generations, inform and share Creole culture with others, serve the community and assists student with their transition into the University system, whether they are incoming freshmen or transfer students. CK has bi-weekly general body meetings and hosts exciting and enriching events! Socials, bowling, skating, community service, volunteering, study nights, Kompa/Zouk nights, cooking and dance workshops, talent shows, forums, road trips and so much more!! Our most popular and well attended event is Soiree Kreyol. Soiree Kreyol or "Soiree" is a formal cultural banquet and fundraiser that brings the Orlando and Creole community together to experience a showcase of culture and delicious food ending with a night of dancing! Guests from all over Florida come to Orlando to enjoy Soiree. One word that represents Club Kreyol is family. In all that we do, we value the importance of creating a comfortable atmosphere where students can make connections that help them succeed in their careers and in life. Family is the foundation of society and the foundation of Creole culture and everyone is welcome in the CK Family.

organizations.name: Knights' Chariots
organizations.description: The mission of Knights' Chariots is to unite Auto Enthusiasts in a community where members share experience, knowledge, and passion for all vehicles.    Be safe, have fun, create a common automotive enthusiast culture, and network with fellow students and facilities.

organizations.name: Reformed University Fellowship
organizations.description: Meeting of students for the purpose of fellowship in a safe environment centered around the Christian faith.

organizations.name: UCF Homecoming
organizations.description: Homecoming is a week full of exciting events for UCF students, alumni, faculty, and staff alike! As the one of the most beloved traditions on campus, Homecoming strives to create events celebrating school spirit, togetherness and inclusion. Our mission is to make UCF Homecoming the best week of the year by bringing people together. Charge on!   2025 Executive Board Executive Director - Gabby Murison|ucfhc@ucf.edu Associate Director - Delaney Warner|hcad@ucf.edu Talent Director  - Grace Paolo|hctalent@ucf.edu Movie Director - Hunter Davis|hcmovie@ucf.edu Comedy Director - Derek Freitas|hccomedy@ucf.edu Concert Director - Ben Lance|hcmusic@ucf.edu Splash Director - Cooper Foxman|hcsplash@ucf.edu Royalty Director - Ari Peters|hccourt@ucf.edu Engagement Director - Christian Jones|hc-engagement@ucf.edu Volunteer Director - Ashleigh Miller|hcvolunteer@ucf.edu Marketing Director - Mya Hauser|hcmarketing@ucf.edu If you have any questions, comments, or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact us!

organizations.name: Pre-Pathology Society
organizations.description: The Pre-Pathology Society (PPS) at UCF is a student-led organization dedicated to exploring the hidden world of pathology, the science behind diagnosing disease and uncovering truth in medicine and forensics. We give students an inside look at careers that often go unnoticed but are critical to healthcare, justice, and research. What sets PPS apart is our Path to Pathology (P2P) Program , a semester-long mentorship track designed to help students build the academic and professional foundation for medical or graduate school. Through resume/CV workshops, advising on degree planning, and personalized guidance, members gain tangible progress toward their goals while earning recognition through our PPS medallion ceremony.   Our members also benefit from: Guest speakers and networking with pathologists, forensic professionals, and medical scientists Research opportunities in pathology-related labs at UCF and beyond Volunteering and outreach with community partners like medical examiners' offices and nonprofit organizations Professional development including graduate/medical school preparation, shadowing, and leadership experience   PPS is more than just a club, it's a launchpad for students fascinated by disease, justice, and the science that brings hidden stories to light. Whether you dream of becoming a physician, forensic pathologist, or biomedical researcher, PPS equips you with the tools, experiences, and community to turn curiosity into impact.   Make sure to join our groupme! https://groupme.com/join_group/97598545/wbGtYH2g

organizations.name: Nexus at UCF
organizations.description: Produced at UCF, Nexus is a premier business podcast featuring in-depth conversations with industry pioneers, scholars, leaders, and global change-makers. We dive into emerging trends, strategies, and the evolving landscape of business to equip students, professionals, and entrepreneurs with the insights needed to navigate the complexities of today, and prepare for the opportunities and challenges of tomorrow. Whether it's revolutionizing industry or reshaping organizational practices, these real-world stories and insights offer a fresh perspective on innovation, impact, and the breakthroughs that occur when visionary thinking meets the pace of modern innovation. Join us as we connect you to the future of business.

organizations.name: American Society of Civil Engineers at the University of Central Florida
organizations.description: ASCE UCF offers civil engineering students activities ranging from tailgates and social events to networking, resume building, and career advancement opportunities. Our general meetings include invited professional speakers who talk about their experience in the industry and often discuss available internships and jobs within their companies. Every year we attend the Annual Southeast Student Symposium, where we compete in over 16 competitions across all civil engineering disciplines! It is a great opportunity to gain some hands-on experience while getting to compete against other schools! Feel free to contact us at asce.ucf@gmail.com if you have any questions! Please visit our website for all our information! Join our free, No-Credit Webcourses class *ASCE UCF does not use Knight's Connect as a primary mode of communication, please use our discord to interact with the club* Become a member now!

organizations.name: First Generation Medicine
organizations.description: The mission of First Generation Medicine is to provide first-generation students with the tools necessary to become impactful leaders within the field of medicine (e.g., physician, dentist, nurse, PT, PA). First Gen. Med. empowers members through mentorship, volunteering, experiential learning, and more. Ultimately, our mission is to foster a diverse community that leads to personal and professional growth for our leaders of tomorrow.

organizations.name: Collegiate National Association for Music Education
organizations.description: NAfME Collegiate at the University of Central Florida is dedicated to advancing music education for our members, school, and the surrounding communities. We strive to promote the art of music through professional development, advocacy, fellowship and service.

organizations.name: Fashion Society @ UCF
organizations.description: What is Fashion Society? We are an all inclusive club that is determined to create a safe space for any and all student creatives interested in the fashion industry. Our focus is on creating a judgement free zone and in making a positive difference within the industry, giving students of all majors the opportunity to dive into a successful career in fashion. We specialize in 9 main committees being Beauty, Design, Modeling, Photography, Production, Social Media, Styling, Web Design,  and  Zine. All of these committee work together throughout the year in order to produce a professional fashion show in the spring semester!     About the Committees Each committee focuses on a different area within the industry where members are given a creative space to work on their craft, together they demonstrate that the fashion industry is often a team of creatives.  Design Committee: responsible for half of the outfits for our spring fashion show. This committee focuses on starting from a design sketch that comes to life through methods such as sewing, knitting, crocheting, etc. Styling Committee: responsible for half of the outfits for our spring fashion show. This committee focuses on sourcing clothing pieces to create members' unique sketches. Photography Committee: responsible for capturing the creative concepts for the chosen theme of the show. This committee includes all photographers and videographers who are looking to increase their portfolio and skillset with opportunities for promo shoots, workshops, and shooting our final show. (you will also be working with the Zine committee in the Fall semester to create our mini magazine) Modeling Committee:  responsible for walking in our spring fashion show. You will be coached on creating your perfect walk and building your confidence on the runway. There will also be modeling opportunities in the form of photo shoots.  Beauty Committee: responsible for all makeup and hair looks needed for our spring fashion show and any promotional shoot done for the club. Production Committee: responsible for all production works to ensure smooth operation of all fashion society events, most importantly our spring show. This includes creating the playlist for the show, coordinating all guests and models for the show, and maintaining our Eventbrite page for all merch/ticket sales. Social Media Committee: responsible for maintaining our Instagram and TikTok accounts. This committee will be in charge of taking behind the scene pictures at all events, managing our Google Drive for all photos, and creating all posts/captions on strict timeline. Website Design Committee: responsible for coding and creating our website where all our events, photos, and updates will be posted. This committee also will be updating the website as the year progresses, and you will act as a liaison between the website developers and the other committees for content. Zine Committee: responsible for creating our mini magazine, from organizing photo shoots (with the help of Photography committee) to collecting student works to designing spreads. **NOTE: this committee is ONLY working in the fall semester. This will give you the opportunity to also work on the show in the spring semester. Committees often participate interactively via sewing or DIY workshops, club-wide photoshoots, socials, and more!  If you have any questions, please DM us on Instagram: @fashionsocietyucf. Be sure to follow our socials for any/all club updates!

organizations.name: Omega Phi Alpha National Service Sorority
organizations.description: As a co-ed sorority, the mission of Omega Phi Alpha is service. We provide opportunities for leadership and friendship through training and participation in service activities. Our hope is that our members will become life-long, service-minded leaders. We strive to better the lives of others worldwide by collaborating with organizations and volunteering trough a flexible service program.

organizations.name: Model United Nations UCF
organizations.description: Model United Nations at the University of Central Florida is UCF's Model United Nations team. UCFMUN is a student organization in which students can learn about the United Nations, international relations, and the vastly diverse cultures and countries from around the world. Every year, the UCF delegation travels nationwide to participate in several Model UN conferences. UCFMUN is an award-winning delegation that has, in the past, participated at conferences such as DawgMUN (University of Georgia), SunMUN (University of Florida), NCSC (Georgetown University), McMUN (McGill University in Quebec), NoleMUN (Florida State University), and more. Besides attending conferences, UCFMUN hosts KnightMUN, a yearly Model UN conference for high school students. The mission of KnightMUN is to provide an environment where students can engage in meaningful discourse, hone their leadership and collaboration skills, and gain a deeper understanding of global issues.  To stay updated, please follow our Instagram (@ucfmodelun) and join our Discord group! We are a students-only group, and no previous Model UN experience is needed. You are also welcome to email our President at unaucfpres@gmail.com if you have any questions! https://discord.com/invite/FZGbGEHk5S

organizations.name: Asian Pacific American Coalition
organizations.description: The Asian Pacific American Coalition (APAC) was founded in 2005 to be a source of social and political advocacy concerning Asian Americans. Since then, it has worked tirelessly to help the Asian and Asian/Pacific Islander American community at the University of Central Florida.  It is open to all UCF students,  and not just those of Asian race. The main goals of APAC are to develop diversity and awareness concerning Asian and Asian Americans, create dedicated, educated, and well rounded members who will use their talents to benefit the greater community, create and participate in community service activities, and be a source of social and political advocacy. The way through which APAC achieves these goals are through a variety of leadership programs and worships, general body meetings, showcase events, and a strong membership body.

organizations.name: UCF Recreation and Wellness Center
organizations.description: The mission of the UCF Recreation and Wellness Center is to foster healthy lifestyle choices and wellness through efficient services, comprehensive programs and high-quality facilities.  The Recreation and Wellness Center is designed to enrich campus life and advance the university's educational mission.

organizations.name: Transfer Center
organizations.description: The Transfer Center is the hub for all transfer students on-campus to get assistance, meet with their Success Coaches, access opportunities and educational experiences, and interact with fellow transfer students. Our events are open to all students. Find us on the main campus at the Trevor Colbourn Hall, Suite 215.

organizations.name: Dominican Student Association
organizations.description: The Dominican Student Association at the University of Central Florida is dedicated to creating a welcoming and inclusive environment where students with roots in the Dominican Republic can feel a strong sense of community. Our mission is to provide a "home away from home" for individuals who share a connection to Dominican culture, creating relationships that are built on pride, unity, and support. Through exciting activities, cultural events, academic initiatives, and volunteer work, we aim to not only celebrate our heritage but also give back to the community while promoting academic and personal growth. We are a family committed to preserving and sharing the richness of Dominican culture, and what better way to celebrate than to be a part of DSA. ¡Qué orgullo ser Dominicano!

organizations.name: Global Medical Training University of Central Florida
organizations.description: Global Medical Training (GMT) is an International Humanitarian Organization that provides free medical/dental services to medically deprived communities in Central American countries. Students will gain hands-on experience in a medical environment, observing and actively participating in patient care. We HIGHLY recommend following us on Instagram for further updates: @ucfgmt

organizations.name: Geotechnical Engineering Institute
organizations.description: Mission The mission of Geotechnical Engineering Institute is to provide an arena and organization to pursue, discuss, and collaborate research interests in an educational and constructive environment while developing leadership, interpersonal, and technical presentation skills required as a future professional geotechnical engineer. Goals Enhance awareness of the geotechnical engineering profession among students. Provide an arena to discuss current events and new methodologies among peers. Foster an exciting learning environment with a goal of professional development.

organizations.name: Lighthouse Haven
organizations.description: The mission of Lighthouse Haven is to uplift and empower pediatric cancer patients through meaningful connection, creative experiences, and personal mentorship.  Inspired by the steadfast presence of a lighthouse, Lighthouse Haven aims to be a place of comfort and hope as they navigate life's most challenging moments.

organizations.name: AmeriCorps VISTA at UCF
organizations.description: AmeriCorps VISTA members are passionate and committed to their mission to bring individuals and communities out of poverty. Members make a year-long, full-time commitment to serve on a specific project at a nonprofit organization or public agency. They focus their efforts to build the organizational, administrative, and financial capacity of organizations that fight illiteracy, improve health services, foster economic development, and otherwise assist low-income communities.  Where will you do your year of service?

organizations.name: Zeta Beta Tau Fraternity, Inc.
organizations.description: ZBT prides itself on being an inclusive Jewish organization welcoming of any college man who understands and appreciates our Mission. ZBT will recruit and initiate men of good character ‚Äî regardless of religion, race or creed ‚Äî who are accepting of our Credo and Mission . Founded in 1898, ZBT is the world's first and largest Jewish Fraternity. Since our historic founding, more than 140,000 men have been initiated into our great Brotherhood. Again making history, in 1989 ZBT became the first fraternity to abolish pledging and all two-tier membership statuses. Our Brotherhood focuses on equal rights, privileges and responsibilities for all brothers. We firmly stand against all forms of hate in our communities, and we are working to create a safer and more inclusive college and community environment for all students.

organizations.name: American Society of Heating, Refrigerating, and Air-Conditioning Engineers
organizations.description: ASHRAE at the University of Central Florida is a student run organization with the purpose to help students get involved in the industry of the Built Environment. Engaging students in learning sustainable building, energy, and mechanical design. ASHRAE at UCF hopes to give students a competitive advantage when they graduate from college as it is directly connected to ASHRAE Central Florida Chapter as well as chapters all over the country and in other parts of the world. In college meetings, educational presentations are given about different areas of the industry such as: Energy Modeling, Energy Audits and management, Building Commissioning, and MEP (Mechanical, Electrical, and Plumbing) Design. Student members also participate in tours of mechanical systems at UCF and in various establishments around Orlando (i.e. the Orange County Convention Center). ASHRAE at UCF is also invited to the local professional chapter's dinner meetings and networking events where students can network with local industry for great internship and work opportunities. Additionally, the student chapter has continuously attended ASHRAE's Winter Conference held every year in different parts of the country (Las Vegas, Chicago, New York City,...etc). Senior standing mechanical engineering students have the opportunity to participate in the annual ASHRAE competition through UCF's senior design projects sponsored by ASHRAE.

organizations.name: Bridges International
organizations.description: Who we are   Bridges is a multi-ethnic, multicultural international student club for students of all nations around the world. While essentially a Christian service organization, our goal is to welcome and serve students of all faiths and backgrounds. Our community is based on these "Four S's":  Social connections among various cultures Service to international students in practical ways and to the community Spiritual resources and life topic conversations Student leadership opportunities to grow as global leaders for the future   Ways to get involved   We do english conversation hours, cultural events, small group get-togethers, evening social game nights on campus, holiday invitations to local American families' homes, and more. We serve all UCF campuses by helping provide rides as needed to connect students from Rosen and Downtown campuses.   Come join us every other Friday evening at Bridges Cafe! 5:30-7:30@GlobalUCF Students from many different countries hang out, play games, have snacks and coffee/tea, make new friends. Just for fun and community!

organizations.name: Philosophy Society at UCF
organizations.description: The mission of the Philosophy Society at UCF is to explore philosophical thought from various intellectual traditions and to engage with peers in open and constructive discussion. We meet in PSY 226 on Fridays at 6pm.   Discord Invite:  https://discord.gg/WcbYnj7TM9 Instagram: ucfphisci

organizations.name: Phi Delta Phi Legal Honor Society
organizations.shortName: Phi Delta Phi Œ¶ŒîŒ¶ ‚Äì UCF Hall
organizations.description: Phi Delta Phi International Legal Honor Society ΦΔΦ ‚Äì UCF Hall seeks to promote scholarship, integrity, ethical conduct and excellence while preparing interested students for law school upon graduation.     Phi Delta Phi¬©¬Æ is the oldest legal organization in continuous existence in the United States, predating even the American Bar Association. It was founded in 1869 at the University of Michigan School of Law by four law students, who at the urging of their faculty, endeavored to create an association that would foster scholarship, civility, and ethical conduct in our profession. Since that time, Phi Delta Phi¬©¬Æ has grown beyond the borders of the United States to Canada, Latin America and Europe.   Phi Delta Phi¬©¬Æ celebrates academic excellence and embraces the finest attributes of professionalism and scholarship. Since our founding, Phi Delta Phi¬©¬Æ has emphasized to students and lawyers alike the importance of our calling. Our active membership is drawn from those students of the law who not only have shown themselves companionable, but have manifested ability and industry in legal study   ucfpdp.com http://www.phideltaphi.org/     Find us on Facebook @  Phi Delta Phi UCF Hall Find us on Instagram @ UCFPhiDeltaPhi     Meetings for Fall 2023 are TBD. Follow the Instagram for more information.

organizations.name: Women in Lasers and Optics
organizations.description: The mission of WiLO is to promote and support women's personal and professional growth in the field of Optics, Photonics and Lasers though community building, networking opportunities, and encouraging young women to choose optics and lasers as a career. This organization will also work towards preparing all CREOL students and students in STEM enrolled in undergraduate and graduate degrees for the transition from student to professional life. Follow us on Instagram and join our Slack for updates!

organizations.name: Delta Phi Omega Sorority, Inc.
organizations.description: The purpose of Delta Phi Omega shall be to foster unity among South Asian women, build community awareness, and gain a greater understanding of oneself and others. The sorority aspires to instill leadership traits, excel in all academic endeavors, to encourage an active relationship between the sorority and its respective university, and shall do so with the utmost compassion, dignity, and fortitude.

organizations.name: Knights Special Events Society
organizations.description: We are a free, student-run organization, the student club associated with ILEA (International Live Events Association). KSES exposes UCF students to the event industry and is an excellent opportunity to learn more about possible career paths with events.   We have monthly meetings, including local industry guest speakers, site visits, workshops, volunteer activities, tours, etc! Some of last year's meetings included guest speaker Lindsey Brinson from Camping World Stadium, a tour and information session with Bill Dewitz from Encore, and while doing several site visits to places like Camping World Stadium, Orlando Convention Center, and Vu Orlando! Our meetings are a great way to immerse yourself in the event world and will allow you to learn and network with local professionals from all realms of the industry.   Since we are the ILEA Orlando student club, KSES members have the fantastic opportunity to become an ILEA Student Member. You can be an ILEA Student Member for all four years, and we highly recommend it for Juniors and Seniors; student membership, however, is open to everyone! The benefits of becoming a member are endless and include being able to attend ILEA meetings, being a full member of the national society, and networking- to name a few! KSES will also notify you of numerous volunteer opportunities with ILEA so you can gain experience, which is a critical aspect of being successful in the event industry. The typical annual ILEA membership cost is approximately $500, but as a Student Member with KSES, the price is significantly reduced to only $50! Being an ILEA student member is not a requirement for KSES, but we strongly encourage it as it will provide you with excellent opportunities and is great for your resume and future success.

organizations.name: Pre-Veterinary Society
organizations.description: Welcome to the Pre-Veterinary Society at the University of Central Florida! As Pre-Veterinary students dedicated to entering a competitive field, this organization provides a means for learning about the academic process and the opportunities available within this career. As a member of the PVS, students are given the chance to network with their peers and veterinary professionals. We are nationally affiliated with the American Pre-Veterinary Medical Association (APVMA) and winner of the "APVMA 2012 Oustanding Club Community Service Award". Be sure to join us on Instagram and Facebook ! And   explore our website  to learn more about us and to discover helpful resources for pre-veterinary students.

organizations.name: Hominids Anonymous
organizations.description: We are the official Undergraduate Anthropology Club at UCF! We are passionate about anthropology and welcome anyone who shares this passion, no matter your major. We have lots of events throughout the semester, including anthropology trivia, movie nights, socials, museum tours, stone tool pumpkin carving, and more! Be sure to check back often for new events! Also follow us on our socials below to keep informed on all the hominids action! For more information, contact Jacob Gelman (President) at ja549890@ucf.edu or email us at hominidsanonymousucf@gmail.com! We are always happy to answer any questions you may have so please don't hesitate to reach out!

organizations.name: CHAARG at UCF
organizations.description: 2 out of 3 college women don't feel comfortable going to the weight room... CHAARG is here to change that!  CHAARG started because we saw the divide between the weight room + cardio machines... + noticed that many women did not feel confident in the gym! Our mission is to "liberate girls from the elliptical" + show them that fitness can [+ should!] be FUN... + that working out is better with friends!   Once you join CHAARG, you are welcomed into a supportive + empowering community of 10,000+ members! Every week, you'll try a different fitness class ‚Äî like: pilates, kickboxing, cardio dance, + more! When you workout, you'll feel good ‚Äî but, when you surround yourself with people to support you, you'll feel even better. CHAARG combines great friends + fun workouts to help every member feel their best.   Memberships are open all year! Once purchased, feel free to come to any of our events! Join officially at  shop.chaarg.com  + make sure to follow us on Instagram @ucf_inchaarg to stay updated <3

organizations.name: Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc.
organizations.description: On January 13, 1974 a group of women met with representatives of Florida Technological University (UCF's former name) to determine which National Black sorority to affiliate with. By a majority vote meeting attendees decided they would affiliate with Delta Sigma Theta Sorority Incorporated. On May 16, 1975 the Mu Iota chapter of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority Inc., was chartered as the FIRST BLACK GREEK LETTERED ORGANIZATION of any kind on UCF's campus. The Sorority was founded in 1913 by 22 students at Howard University. These young women wanted to use their collective strength to promote academic excellence; to provide scholarships; to provide support to the underserved; educate and stimulate participation in the establishment of positive public policy; and to highlight issues and provide solutions for problems in their communities.  The major programs of the sorority are based upon the organization's Five Point Programmatic Thrust: Economic Development Educational Development International Awareness and Involvement Physical and Mental Health Political Awareness and Involvement

organizations.name: Catholic Campus Ministry
organizations.description: Catholic Campus Ministry at the University of Central Florida is a community of missionary disciples whose relationships create a home for Christian life as a spiritual family living in the heart of the Church.   Our Core Values: - Belief in Jesus - Wholehearted Worship - Relational Evangelization - Brotherhood and Sisterhood - Formation to Christian Maturity - Transformational Community - Renewal in the Holy Spirit   Join us on Slack, find Retreat Registrations, join our Outreach Teams, and much more through our LinkTree  and Instagram   Join us weekly for Confession at 4:30pm and Mass at 5pm Tuesday-Thursday at the Catholic Center @ Northview during the Fall and Spring semesters. We close when UCF closes typically!

organizations.name: Tower II Apartments
organizations.description: Area Council is a student led group in your own residence that will be active in leadership, programming, and advocacy for the community. The mission is to provide a residence life program that encourages a positive living and learning environment, supportive of students development in the college community by providing quality opportunities and connections for academic and personal growth.

organizations.name: The National Council of Negro Women
organizations.description: 2025-2026  Initiative : N-VINCIBLE           Founded by Dr. Mary McLeod Bethune in 1935, the National Council of Negro Women, Incorporated (NCNW) played an important role in the struggle for human and civil rights all contributing to the peaceful solutions to the problems of human welfare and rights.           The National Council of Negro Women, Incorporated (NCNW) is a non-profit organization with the mission to advance the opportunities and quality of life for women, families, and communities. NCNW fulfills this mission through research, advocacy, national and community-based services, and programs.           NCNW was founded at the University of Central Florida by Charlyn Stanberry in the summer of 2005. Here at UCF, our mission is to Lead, Develop and Advocate not only on campus but in the greater community through community service and events to raise awareness. Follow us on all social media @NCNWUCF for upcoming events!

organizations.name: Campus Crusade for Christ
organizations.description: Mission Cru at UCF is a welcoming community that loves Jesus and wants him to be known on campus.  Our goal is that every student at UCF would know someone who loves Jesus. Description Welcome to Cru at UCF. Here you can find new friends, fun, laughter, leadership development, diverse students, community, mission, opportunities to serve the campus of UCF, teaching, discussion, live music, and all kinds of things throughout the week on campus and off campus! You are invited to enjoy, participate and lead in this movement that exists here at UCF to build relationships and create spaces where you can experience the life and message of Jesus.    Ways to Get Involved  1. Cru Thursday is the weekly meeting of Cru @ UCF. We invite you to join us every Thursday evening as we seek to experience God through relationship and real-life teaching from the Bible. Our goal is to energize, encourage, and ignite a passion for loving God and others.   2. Community groups are the way that we connect with our living communities in smaller group setting. It's where we grow in our relationship with Christ and each other. These happen throughout the week.   For more details, visit our website or follow us on Instagram. Our handle is @cruatucf.

organizations.name: Hercules Community
