organizations.description: To provide a residence life program that encourages a positive living and learning environment, supportive of students development in the college community by providing quality opportunities and connections for academic and personal growth.   Hercules Area Council meets every Thursday from 5:00pm-6:00pm in the Hercules Activity Center!

organizations.name: Knightmare Bhangra
organizations.description: The goal of Knightmare Bhangra at UCF is to have a vibrant and spirited dance group that seeks to celebrate the rich heritage of Bhangra while fostering school spirit, sportsmanship, and community engagement. As a dynamic ensemble of talented dancers, our mission is to entertain and inspire audiences at various university events, community gatherings in the Orlando area, and exhilarating dance competitions held at local, state-wide, and national levels.

organizations.name: Big Sister Little Sister Mentoring Program
organizations.description: Big Sister Little Sister is a National Mentoring Program with a global impact. BSLS promotes life skills, mental health, and principles of self with a focus on personal and professional development. We strive to make a positive and lasting impact on school campuses, in communities, and in the lives of youth and women.

organizations.name: Society of Hispanic Professional Engineers
organizations.description: Welcome to the official Knight Connect page for SHPE at UCF! The Society of Hispanic Professional Engineers (SHPE) was founded in Los Angeles, California, in 1974 by a group of engineers employed by the city of Los Angeles. Their objective was to form a national organization of professional engineers to serve as role models in the Hispanic community. This organization made its way to Orlando in 1988. Our Chapter focuses on the Hispanic population at the University of Central Florida. For our members, we offer workshops, discussion panels, information sessions, and much more to prepare our soon-to-be Engineers for the real world. Companies come to our Chapter to discuss a multitude of topics, such as how to write a winning resume, interviewing tips/techniques and what companies expect out of an entry-level Engineer. SHPE National's mission is to empower the Hispanic community, so we took it upon our Chapter to engage with the younger community around Orlando to inform them about the importance of STEM. We conduct school visits to middle and high schools through our SHPE Junior Program to present what technical professions are and how they affect our everyday life. We also monitor student competitions for SECME, a statewide program that enables younger student with hands-on projects with basic math and science applications. With almost 400 members, every day we're closer to reaching the entire Hispanic STEM community at the University of Central Florida. We are devoted to empowering our members to realize their fullest potential and to impact the world through STEM awareness, access, support, and development. Leadership is a key element for SHPE and we encourage all members to become leaders within our organization. It's not only a great experience, but it allows you meet other students and Chapters.   SHPE UCF: En la Florida Central, ¡Juntos sin parar! Register with us to become a member: Membership Registration Form Make sure to connect with us on our socials: Discord | Instagram | Website | LinkedIn

organizations.name: Neg Kreyol, Inc.
organizations.description: Neg Kreyol is a non-profit student organization which focuses on benefiting other Haitian Organizations, the Haitian community and Haiti. The plan is to collaborate up with other nonprofits to help raise awareness and aid for Haiti. Members will gain leadership experience and a brotherhood within the organization while networking with members of other student organizations and business leaders of the community.

organizations.name: Hispanic Student Association
organizations.description: Hola, mi gente! We are the Hispanic Student Association here at the University of Central Florida! As an RSO, our goal is to become a safe haven for all Hispanic students at UCF. We hope that they can find a home and community within the Hispanic Student Association, as we want them to be able to share the beauty that their cultures have to offer with no judgment. We also hope to share what each person has to offer culturally with the rest of the university so that everyone may gain knowledge and information.    Follow us on Instagram @hsa.ucf for updates on meetings and other events!!

organizations.name: National Student Speech Language Hearing Association (NSSLHA) - Orlando
organizations.description: HOW TO BECOME A UCF NSSLHA MEMBER NOTE: Membership applications for Fall 2025 will open on August 11th, 2025!   Step 1. Request NSSLHA membership on Knight Connect (Click 'Join' on our page) Knight Connect provides you with access to emails from the organization, your service record, and events such as our General Body Meetings, and more!   Step 2. Complete the appropriate e-application and submit your chapter dues (link in application) Please Note: requests are approved during the following application acceptance windows: Membership applications are open from August 11th, 2025  through October 10th, 2025! Undergraduate Application:  https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSccN4a0J4-GlA15R6vO5RlezP6iOjbbCUSnH2IWC-x1QyTWQg/viewform?usp=dialog Graduate Application: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScxygOasX8aRXVdzcatP2GMqsBsvPdzZYicVivaQrB9ezgXnw/viewform?usp=header   Step 3 . Once we receive your e-application and dues, you will be accepted as a member on Knight Connect and are welcome to sign up for events, meetings, and workshops! :) ** Please note that if you are a current/existing member who already has approved access to our Knight Connect page, you still need to complete an application for each school year and pay chapter dues to be considered an "active" NSSLHA member. Otherwise, you will be removed from the roster ** If you have questions about this, please email secretary.ucfnsslha@gmail.com . ** Be sure to visit our website (https://ucfnsslha.com/) and follow us on our social media (see the icons below) to keep up to date and network with members!  What is UCF NSSLHA? The National Student Speech-Language Hearing Association (NSSLHA) Chapter at The University of Central Florida strives to connect members with opportunities to enhance what is learned in the classroom and apply it to real-world observations and participation. Through partnerships with other campus organizations, fundraisers, socials, volunteer opportunities, and guest speakers we provide a plethora of outlets for our members to network with students, and professionals in the Orlando area. What do we do? In the past, we have partnered with the Special Olympics of Florida, Autism Speaks, UCF CARD & UCF PALS, Ronald McDonald House, and groups such as the American Sign Language Club and UCF Best Buddies. Socials for members have included, Lake Claire picnics, ropes courses at the Recreation and Wellness Center, and bowling just to name a few. Guest speakers have included UCF professors, organization representatives, audiologists and SLP's, and individuals experiencing a communication disorder. NSSLHA maintains a close relationship with the School of Communication Sciences and Disorders the UCF Communication Disorders Clinic located in Research Park providing us with many volunteer opportunities and unique experiences that are given exclusively to members. In the upcoming year, we plan to expand the opportunities through more socials, a wider variety of guest speakers, and participation in more campus events.

organizations.name: Women's Rugby Club @ UCF
organizations.description: A club where women of all shapes and sizes can learn and play rugby with other schools throughout the state as well as around the country. No experience is necessary to come play and we practice every Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday from 4:00 pm-6:00 pm in the Fall and Spring on the sports club grass fields.

organizations.name: Knights Pantry
organizations.description: The Knights Helping Knights Pantry is committed to serving the UCF students by providing basic needs for free including food, clothing, and personal hygiene items to foster continued academic success thus increasing retention.

organizations.name: Late Knights
organizations.description: The goal of Late Knights is to provide UCF students with a place to enjoy themselves and unwind with fun, safe, and on-campus events late at night. Late Knights host Weekly Small Scale Events and Monthly Large Scale Events. Our events range from pool parties and paint knights to giveaways and trivia competitions. We feature free food, prizes, and unforgettable entertainment.   Our Weekly Small Scale Events are held on Friday nights and select weekends starting at 7 PM and our Monthly Large Scale Events are often held on Friday or Saturday nights from 8 PM on.    Registered Student Organizations can benefit from Late Knights by either reserving a table to promote and recruit members, or by sponsoring or co-programming an activity at a weekly or monthly event. Each event consistently attracts over 500+ students. We love to share our Late Knights Platform with RSOs, please contact ucflk@ucf.edu for more information.    How To Get Involved If you are interested in getting involved or volunteering with Late Knights, please fill out the 2024-2025 Late Knights Council Application underneath "Forms". You can also email our Associate Director at lkad@ucf.edu for more information!    Mission The mission of Late Knights is to function as a student run agency under the Office of Student Involvement (OSI) whose purpose is to promote safe and unique entertainment options, community engagement, and genuine memories through campus events for all.   Contact Us Nicolas Morales Executive Director ucflk@ucf.edu   Taliah Bannister Associate Director lkad@ucf.edu   Merrick Laird Engagement Director lkengagement@ucf.edu   Hope Davis Marketing Director lkcommunication@ucf.edu   Williamson Surin Programming Director lkprogramming@ucf.edu   Alina Rojas Special Events Director lkspecialevents@ucf.edu     Stay Connected!

organizations.name: Special Olympics College Club at UCF
organizations.description: Special Olympics is a global organization that provides Olympic-style sports training and competition for children and adults with intellectual disabilities. It offers athletes the opportunity to improve their physical fitness, build confidence, and experience joy within a supportive community of fellow Special Olympics athletes. Since its founding in 1968, the mission of Special Olympics has remained the same: "To create a better world by fostering the acceptance and inclusion of all people."   The Special Olympics College Club at UCF is a sports club that fosters friendships between college students and individuals with intellectual disabilities through a shared love of sports. The club also continues to lead the social inclusion movement of Special Olympics. By incorporating the three core components of a Special Olympics College Club‚ÄîUnified Sports, Inclusive Leadership, and Whole School Engagement‚Äîwe aim to help transform college campuses into communities that reflect inclusion and acceptance.   To get updates on events and meetings, follow us on Instagram @ucfspecialolympics  and join our  Discord!  If you have any questions, feel free to message us on any of our platforms or send an email to ucfspecialolympics@gmail.com!

organizations.name: Judo at UCF
organizations.description: To provide students with the opportunity to practice and participate in recreational Judo with the possibility of competing through the National Collegiate Judo Association and/or USA Judo.

organizations.name: Cycling Club @ UCF
organizations.description: PLEASE CONTACT US VIA EMAIL OR IMLEAGUES. Sport Clubs use a new system (IM Leagues) for main contact. If you are interested in joining the club, please search through there or email us/find us on social media so that we can get you connected. We are the Cycling Knights of all disciplines, including road, mountain biking, track, cyclocross, and bmx! If you want to race road or mountain bikes, come join us!  Email or Message us on social media to find out about other local rides! Sport Clubs now function on IM Leagues website, so please contact us there, or our email cyclingclub@ucf.edu

organizations.name: alpha Kappa Delta Phi International Sorority, Inc.
organizations.description: The sisterhood of alpha Kappa Delta Phi provides women with a sense of belonging that nurtures life-long friendships, develops self-empowered leaders, and strengthens communities through our pillars of service, scholarship, sisterhood, leadership, and Asian-Awareness. Since 1999, alpha Kappa Delta Phi's national philanthropy is Breast Cancer Awareness with a goal to raise awareness, educate, and help fund breast cancer research. Through our united efforts to spread awareness year round and during the month of October, our sisters have donated over $1M to help those that have been impacted by this disease.

organizations.name: Volunteer UCF Alternative Break Program
organizations.description: Volunteer UCF's Alternative Break Program places teams of students in communities to engage in service and experiential learning. ABP Teams are exposed to complex social and cultural issues that aim to heighten social awareness, encourage life-long community collaboration, and promote the advocacy of social change within communities. Teams are led by student Coordinators who guide group development before, during, and after the experience. Faculty Advisors also facilitate the experience.   We coordinate domestic service trips with community partners to empower UCF students to be agents of change today and leaders of tomorrow during Winter and Spring Break and possibly some long- weekends.    To stay updated please be sure to follow us on Instagram and check out our linktree, which can be found below. Looking forward to working with you!

organizations.name: Glee Club at UCF
organizations.description: Glee Club at UCF is a non-competitive choir that meets weekly to rehearse group numbers and sing karaoke together. Our rehearsals culminate to our end-of-semester showcases where we show off all that our members have worked on for the past few months. Auditions are held every spring and fall so follow our Instagram for updates and check our KnightConnect page for more information on Glee events!

organizations.name: Arab American Student Association
organizations.description: Our club was founded with a main mission: to build a vibrant community for all Arab Americans at UCF, fostering empathy, understanding, and cultural awareness through active engagement and outreach throughout campus. AASA provides a platform for students to connect with their heritage, share their experiences, and educate the community about Arab culture and traditions. By encouraging dialogue and collaboration, AASA strives to bridge cultural gaps and build a more inclusive campus environment.

organizations.name: Taekwondo Club @ UCF
organizations.description: Welcome to the Taekwondo Club @ UCF! We practice both traditional and Olympic styles of Taekwondo and are always accepting new students from beginners to black belts. Our club represents UCF at local, state, and national competitions in board breaking, poomsae, and sparring. Whether you're looking for a great workout or aiming for team USA, become a member of our Taekwondo family! If you have any questions, feel free to visit our website ,  contact us or come watch a practice!   FALL 2025 PRACTICE SCHEDULE: MONDAY 7 - 9 PM ‚Äî> Sparring Class WEDNESDAY 7 - 9 PM ‚Äî> Traditional Class FRIDAY 7 - 9 PM ‚Äî> Recover & Conquer SATURDAY 10 AM - 12 PM ‚Äî> Weapons SUNDAY 11:30 AM - 1:30 PM ‚Äî> Open Mat   2025 - 2026 OFFICER BOARD: President - Matgelina Mendoza Risk Manager -  Anthony McFarlin Treasurer -  Kaleb Grady Event Coordinator -  Kennedy Taylor Secretary -  Damian Ortiz Diaz Public Relations Director -  Diego Growe Head Instructor -   Quentin Cates

organizations.name: Beta Alpha Psi Honorary Accounting Organization
organizations.description: Beta Alpha Psi is an honorary accounting organization that strives to help candidates and members in their professional development and prepare them for successful careers in the accounting field. Each semester Beta Alpha Psi hosts a variety of events including: workshops, meetings, mock interviews and socials with accounting firms to accomplish this goal.    Beta Alpha Psi offers you:  - Professional reputation  - Mentors - Networking opportunities with firms and peers - Soft skills development    Stay up to date with the latest BAP news by liking our Facebook page: Beta Alpha Psi at UCF or check out our website: bapucf.com

organizations.name: Society for Human Resource Management
organizations.description: SHRM Student Chapter at UCF is an undergraduate and graduate service chapter that promotes education, networking, and leadership opportunities for Human Resource majors, Business majors, and non-business majors. Our board of officers strive to provide the best connections on campus and in the community to help students find job placement, internships, volunteer opportunities, and overall experience to separate themselves more marketable. Throughout the semester, we invite local business professionals from various backgrounds to share their knowledge of current and upcoming trends that will affect the future professional. Outside of meetings, participation as both attendee and volunteer are encouraged at local GOSHRM meetings, HR FL and SHRM conferences, and SHRM Student Chapter at UCF events & activities.

organizations.name: Alpha Tau Omega Fraternity
organizations.description: Alpha Tau Omega is UCF's premier social and leadership fraternity. Since the chapter's establishment in 1971, ΑΤΩ has been a power house on Greek Park. The gentlemen of ΑΤΩ pride themselves in academics, intramural sports, campus involvement and sociability. This diverse group of young leaders pushes the limits every year with record-setting philanthropic events, Greek social events and innovative ways to improve the university and local community. Located at 4419 Greek Ct., Alpha Tau Omega is currently the largest fraternity house on campus. For more information about the chapter, email ato@ucf.edu.

organizations.name: Holistic Living Organization
organizations.description: HLO is a community of growth-oriented individuals who explore the connection of the mind, body, and soul through a holistic approach. Our team vision stands to liberate the community of UCF from the single-dimensional approach to health which prevails in society today and to empower each other with the tools and natural solutions to break free from the shackles of mental, physical, social, and spiritual illness.    We also encourage our community to individually keep their inner & outer environment clean so we can have space for more flow & growth.   We value OPENNESS: Open space, open mind, open heart     Discord: https://discord.gg/h6U9NApn Instagram: ucfholisticlivingorg

organizations.name: Interfraternity Council
organizations.description: Proud to be one of the most encompassing and diverse organizations on campus representing over 1300 fraternity men, these members are held to a higher standard as we work together to build a better community and better men.   The UCF Interfraternity Council (IFC) is part of the North American Interfraternity Council (NIC). The NIC serves to advocate the needs of its members fraternities through enrichment of the fraternity experience; advancement and growth of the fraternity community and enhancement of the educational mission of the host institutions. The NIC is also committed to enhancing the benefits of fraternity membership. At UCF, the Interfraternity Council consists of 12 active national organizations and is continuing to grow. All 12 organizations consistently go throughout their day exemplifying the university‚Äôs creed: Integrity, Scholarship, Community, Creativity, and Excellence. By thinking of these integral aspects of our university, each member of a fraternity in the Interfraternity Council will actively take part in philanthropic activities, community service, educational seminars and conferences, as well as social gatherings with other peers among the school.

organizations.name: Ice Hockey Club @ UCF
organizations.description: Founded in 1997, the Knights Hockey program competes in Division II of the American Collegiate Hockey Association (ACHA) as a member of Collegiate Hockey South (CHS), and also represents the North American Collegiate Hockey League (NACHL). With 12 national championship appearances and two 3rd-place finishes, the team is recognized as both a successful and rapidly growing program. The University of Central Florida Ice Hockey team is passionate about spreading the love of the game, not just on campus, but throughout the state of Florida. As professional hockey continues to thrive in the Sunshine State, interest in the sport at the collegiate level has grown alongside it. As one of the top programs in Collegiate Hockey South, Knights Hockey prides itself on a commitment to excellence, competition, and community. The program offers players the opportunity to compete at a high level while building lasting relationships with teammates, coaches, fans, and supporters, fostering a family atmosphere that lasts a lifetime. Visit our instagram @icehockeyatucf and website https://www.knightshockeyatucf.com/ for more info!

organizations.name: Meeting Professionals International
organizations.description: MPI stands for Meeting Professionals International, and MPI Knights is the student chapter of the larger MPI Orlando chapter.  We create numerous opportunities for our members to network with industry professionals, participate in different site tours , attend panels with guest speakers , and learn through the workshops we host. In addition, we strongly value the connections our members make with one another and provide social and fundraising events to foster and grow the community that is MPI Knights.  MPI Orlando, our parent chapter, is "an organization dedicated to your personal and career success where you'll connect with the innovative learning, passionate people and big ideas that will empower you to become an agent of change and reinvent the world". Becoming a member of MPI Knights will help you build connections with MPI Orlando to attend their monthly meetings, education sessions, and networking events to meet industry professionals and learn more about the event industry. To stay up to date with everything we're doing, follow us on Instagram @mpiknights!

organizations.name: The German Club
organizations.description: The German Club at the University of Central Florida is a cultural organization whose goal is to help students understand and appreciate the German culture and language. The club is open to all students who are interested in learning about a new language and culture - no prior knowledge required. We offer biweekly General Body Meetings that focus on cultural and historical topics, as well as "Kaffeestunde" (coffee hour) get-togethers to practice German conversation in a friendly and casual setting. We also hold several special events throughout the semester such as volunteer opportunities and social gatherings outside of campus.

organizations.name: Knighthawk Audubon
organizations.description: Welcome! We are Knighthawk Audubon, a college campus chapter representing the National Audubon Society at UCF. Our primary goal is to foster interest in ornithology while creating opportunities to see and learn about birds for students. We want to c reate an inclusive and diverse environment for all students to work with the community as well as local Audubon chapters to inspire, promote, and facilitate the conservation of local and national avifauna and their ecosystems. We want to connect students with avian-related activities such as bird-watching hikes along with professional conservation opportunities provided by the National Audubon Society. We hope you will join us to help make the world a better place for birds and their environments!   Are you interested in joining us? Here's our membership info: Join Knighthawk Audubon here on KnightConnect. Join our GroupMe chat and follow our Instagram for additional club updates. Pay membership dues : $15 for one school year or $10 for one semester. You can pay dues through CashApp ($knighthawkaudubonucf) or in-person via cash.  When paying through CashApp, please include your name, UCF e-mail, and shirt size.  Our meetings and off-campus events are open to all members, however, you'll receive numerous benefits as a dues-paying member such as: Eligible to participate in carpools for our off-campus hikes, camping trips, and volunteer events. Eligible to win our "Bird of the Month" raffle prizes. Receive a rad club T-shirt. Chance to earn an exclusive Knighthawk enamel pin.

organizations.name: Wesley at UCF
organizations.description: Wesley at UCF is a non-profit campus ministry that hosts many weekly events that are curated to support students. We are inspired by Dr. Martin Luther King's vision of the "Beloved Community," an inclusive community where everyone belongs. You can find us located on East plaza between the Barnes & Noble and Amazon Locker. Wesley at UCF supports the community by offering the following: Student Lounge: a space for students to have a quiet, clean, and comforting place to study or get free coffee or tea on Monday-Thursday from 10a.m. to 3p.m.  Community Knight: On Wednesday's at 5:30, come by for a free, delicious dinner and a space to meet new people and hangout. We also do fun monthly events/game nights where you can win gift cards to local restaurants, even further supporting the Orlando community! Spiritual and Leadership Development: follow training or discussions led by professionals or Rev. Erwin Lopez or guest speakers over the semester. Counseling: You can choose between our specialists for up to 3 free online sessions of individual counseling (while funds last). Remember, you are not alone and we are here for you.   From semester to semester our events may change, so to best stay up to date, follow us on Instagram @wesleyatucf Here we actively post what's new going on within our ministry. Everyone is welcome to our events, and no registration is required.   Wesley at UCF is a safe space for students of all faiths, gender, race, sexuality, etc. Our mission is to establish a loving and caring community of good people where we can all grow together, whether that be spiritually, emotionally, or physically.

organizations.name: Happiest Club on Earth
organizations.description: The Happiest Club on Earth offers a place where fans of Disney may discuss their interests, offering opportunities to engage in community activities hosted by the club, and fostering the advancement of Disney-related academia among interested student members. The Happiest Club on Earth gives Disney enthusiasts a place to bond with other like-minded students. The Happiest Club on Earth hopes to develop an interest in Disney in students who do not already consider themselves to be fans by introducing them to the beloved Disney parks, films, stories, and characters that have already enriched the lives of millions. NOTE: Please follow our social media to stay connected with the club as we do not utilize Knight Connect

organizations.name: Men of Integrity
organizations.description: The Men of Integrity Founded January 11, 2003 serves to be a pivotal aspect of the community. As a co-ed minority organization we strive to foster the ideals of manhood, perseverance and service while advocating human rights. We are here to build an element of family to those who so dwelling. We strive to foster a mindset of mentorship, leadership, professionalism, unity and most of integrity to the service that we provide to our community.

organizations.name: Florida Engineering Society
organizations.description: To prepare engineering students of all disciplines for the high level of performance and responsibility that is required to succeed in today's job market, while providing the opportunity to develop professional relationships with professional engineers, educators, and peers.

organizations.name: Filipino Student Association
organizations.description: The Filipino Student Association (FSA) at the University of Central Florida is a non-profit organization that promotes the Filipino culture throughout the UCF campus and throughout the community of central Florida. FSA promotes itself by holding meetings and hosting and attending a variety of events such as: Open Mic Knight, Def Talent Jam, Field Day, Sayaw, and Formal. We hope to reach out to the diversified community at the University of Central Florida and to encourage all students and faculty to attend our meetings and various events, as we stay committed to our slogan, "Your Home Away From Home." Our mission is to unify the Filipino student community and other student communities by creating and maintaining a network of information and resources to understand Filipino heritage and to encourage a positive understanding of the Filipino culture. If you are new, scroll down to our documents section to read up about membership and upcoming dates!

organizations.name: Saxophone Club
organizations.description: Saxophone Club works to provide weekly saxophone-based educational opportunities for its members. This is achieved through live performances and masterclasses presented by staff or guest artists.

organizations.name: Health-Link Society
organizations.description: We desire to bring together pre-health students who are passionate about community service and healthcare outreach. We strive to make a meaningful impact by volunteering with local clinics, hospitals, and nonprofits, while also helping members gain valuable hands-on experience in the healthcare field.

organizations.name: Equestrian Club at UCF
organizations.description: The Equestrian Club features three teams: Eventing, Hunt Seat, and Western. While each team is part of the club, they all compete separately. The club meets once a month to discuss horse shows, fundraisers, and volunteering events. We volunteer 3-5 times per year at local animal rescue facilities, horse farms, food shares, and more.

organizations.name: The Last Secret
organizations.description: We're the International Bible Study group known as 'The Last Secret' on the UCF campus. We blend science, history, and scripture to unveil hidden prophecies throughout the Bible. Beyond our studies, we illuminate Orlando through ASEZ volunteer activities. Join us for a thrilling journey of uncovering the secrets of the Bible!

organizations.name: BAPS Campus Fellowship
organizations.description: The purpose of the organization shall be to unite students on University of Central Florida's campus and provide opportunities to learn about Hindu heritage and culture. It will introduce the Hindu faith to the rest of the University of Central Florida community and will foster issues affecting Hindus through youth group discussions, campus events, and community service projects.

organizations.name: Intellectual Decisions on Environmental Awareness Solutions For Us
organizations.description: https://youtu.be/lB6GaA-3gaU

organizations.name: Knights for Refugee Medical Relief
organizations.description: Knights for Refugee Medical Relief (KRMR) works as a community to provide medical and educational relief to refugees. Through volunteering opportunities and fundraising events, our members come together to help local and global refugees.   How do you become part of the KRMR family? ‚ú∫ Join our enthusiastic team with the common goal of strengthening and improving the lives of refugees by becoming an official member of KRMR by filling out the following link:  KRMR Membership Form ‚ú∫ Join our club's group me to meet other members and maintain direct communication: KRMR GroupMe   For more information on KRMR and the current events of KRMR take a look at our Link Tree: KRMR Link Tree

organizations.name: The University Writing Center
organizations.description: The University Writing Center is a campus resource that offers free individual and small-group consultations to UCF community members, for any writing in any situation. Our purpose is not merely to fix papers but to teach writers strategies to understand and to navigate complex situations for writing, both in and outside the University.

organizations.name: CAPS Peer Educators
organizations.description: We are here to educate the campus community on mental fitness and stress reduction. CAPS Peer Educators help guide students to the available resources on campus to help them stay mentally fit. Our goal is to connect with students to help reduce the stigma of seeking mental health services.

organizations.name: UCF Global
organizations.description: UCF Global at the University of Central Florida functions as the primary international hub for students, faculty, and staff. Through strong partnerships UCF Global is committed to increasing international mobility and enhancing the university's global competency. Encompassing the Intensive English Program and multiple support services for the international population on campus, UCF Global aides in transforming the lives of the UCF and global community.

organizations.name: Young Investors Club
organizations.description: General Body Meetings (GBM) : Thursday's 8:00PM, location is BA1-119  Workshops : Tuesday's 7:00PM, location is CB1-119  Registration:  4/23/2025 How to become a member: 1. Dues:  45 for the semester - 70 for the year | Paid via Venmo to @YIC2526 or Cash App $YIC2526  | Add your full name in the notes! 2.Membership Sign-up Form: Complete the short membership form here: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdVGd4fyGouRN8gDexgSzjPk_SFO2xTSR72G0meXAqmEQraXg/viewform?usp=header 3.Access to Discord: Gain access in the discord by typing your name in the dues channel The vision of Young Investors Club is to educate members on how to accumulate wealth, achieve success, and gain financial freedom. This club is the place on campus where the most motivated and knowledgeable investment students at UCF meet to discuss lucrative investment and trading strategies along with portfolio management in the current global and financial markets. We welcome all students, regardless of experience or major, to come and learn sound financial management skills, discover and share ideas, while networking with some of the brightest minds at UCF. Instagram -  http://instagram.com/yic_ucf Discord -  www.dsc.gg/YIC

organizations.name: Crocheting Knights
organizations.description: We are an organization dedicated to bringing together people with a passion for crocheting. We accept all different levels of experience and help new crocheters learn.

organizations.name: Society of Women Engineers
organizations.description: The Society of Women Engineers aims to empower women to aspire, advance, and succeed as engineers and leaders. Our section hosts various events each month to encourage members to develop themselves professionally and academically, while also meeting other important women in engineering.

organizations.name: Delta Epsilon Chi
organizations.description: Collegiate DECA prepares emerging leaders and entrepreneurs in marketing, finance, hospitality, accounting, etc in colleges around the globe. This is done through role play competitions events that gives students experience in public speaking and real business scenarios. We have various guest speakers, competition prep, resume, LinkedIn, and powerpoint workshops throughout the semester.

organizations.name: American Physical Society Chapter at University of Central Florida
organizations.description: The mission and goals of the American Physical Society Chapter at University of Central Florida are similar to the mission and goals outlined by APS: APS Chapters seek to support the development of undergraduates, graduate students and early-career individuals as colleagues and future leaders. To achieve these goals and build cohesive communities that will strengthen the discipline, we will: Develop opportunities for networking and for career and professional development Empower individuals to build and promote inclusive and equitable communities Support learning and practice for all, including those from underrepresented groups Inform and facilitate engagement on policy issues impacting the profession

organizations.name: Central Florida Cello Association
organizations.description: The goal of Central Florida Cello Association is to heighten the exposure of its members by interacting with successful individuals in the industry through masterclasses, recitals, and workshops. Members will also be given the opportunity to perform at venues they otherwise would not have access to in their early career, alongside being able to experience performances they otherwise would not have available to them.

organizations.name: Colombian Student Association
organizations.description: The goals of ColSA are to bring Colombian students at UCF together to help and support one another throughout their academic experience at UCF; to provide a means for Colombian students to relax and enjoy their college experience; to help incoming students adjust to campus life; to showcase our heritage and culture to the student body; to promote harmony and build bridges of friendship and understanding between the UCF community and Colombian students; to be an inclusive organization that welcomes non-Colombian student membership; and to become a point of contact and exchange between Colombia (schools, universities, community, organizations, etc.) and UCF.

organizations.name: Wellness and Health Promotion Services
organizations.description: Wellness & Health Promotion Services (WHPS) offers a wide variety of services and programs aimed at helping all UCF students be healthy knights! We promote healthy lifestyle habits associated with higher academic performance by providing outreach and educational workshops on safe sex, nutrition, stress management, sleep, healthy relationships, and body image. To support student safety, we provide HIV Testing and Risk Reduction Counseling. We offer Biofeedback assisted relaxation training to help students manage stress. We coordinate the Healthy Knights 2020 initiative, an SDES collaborative effort focused on promoting the overall health of all UCF students. To learn more about any of the topics mentioned check out our Health Huts seen around campus, or follow us on Facebook/Twitter/Instagram/YouTube/Pinterest @HealthyKnight

organizations.name: Student Conduct and Academic Integrity
organizations.description: Student Conduct and Academic Integrity (SCAI), a division of the Office of Student Rights and Responsibilities, provides educational opportunities that foster individual growth, ethical development and personal accountability while promoting the core values of the university: integrity, scholarship, community, creativity, and excellence.

organizations.name: Human Factors and Ergonomics Society - Student Chapter
organizations.description: As the student chapter for the Human Factors and Ergonomics Society (HFES) at the University of Central Florida, we serve as the advocate and official representative of our members, and add to the prestige of our University and the discipline of human factors and ergonomics.  We strive to assist students with professional development, by providing unique networking opportunities, by bringing in guest speakers, and creating speaker panels for discussion.  Additionally, we disseminate information in order to increase awareness of human factors and ergonomics at the local, state, national, and international level. Our organization provides a forum for discussion of issues relevant to human factors and ergonomics, in order to foster students' understanding and involvement within the field.  We assist our members in establishing and working toward achieving scientific, professional, and educational objectives based on tradition, innovation, and integrity.

organizations.name: First Love Church
organizations.description: First Love Church UCF is part of the First Love Church, a vibrant, youthful Christian ministry founded by Bishop Dag Heward-Mills in Ghana. First Love is passionate about Jesus, soul-winning, and serving God wholeheartedly. The movement started with university students and has grown into a global church with thousands of members. At UCF, we continue this mission by creating a welcoming space for young people to grow in faith, encounter God through worship, and be empowered by His Word. Our services and fellowship provide an opportunity for students to experience God's love, deepen their relationship with Christ, and actively share the gospel on campus.

organizations.name: Officials Association at the University of Central Florida
Future Leaders of the Lodging Industry
Kappa Alpha Theta Fraternity
organizations.description: Founded in 1870 at Indiana Asbury (now DePauw University) in Greencastle, Ind., Kappa Alpha Theta is the first Greek-letter Fraternity known among women. In creating Kappa Alpha Theta, our founders were leading the way for women's groups and for women in higher education. Our members are women of all ages: women who attended college in nearly every US state and Canadian province, women who live all over the world, and women with varied professions, faiths, and ethnic backgrounds.

organizations.name: Graduate Health Network
organizations.description: The Graduate Health Network is a student organization on campus that strives to give one of a kind opportunities to students seeking a career in Healthcare Management. Each semester, we set goals to connect current health leaders to the needs of the current members that will enhance the understanding of their specific area of interest. To balance out the ample amount of knowledge gained not only through our education through UCF but also the educational events on campus, GHN makes it a priority to have social and networking events each semester for all members and their guests to enjoy each others company, and foster a community within our MHA program here at UCF. Don't miss out on a great opportunity for your career, or simply a great networking opportunity and join the Graduate Health Network TODAY!! Be sure to connect with us here through KnightConnect to become an official member and follow us on Social media to stay up-to-date with our upcoming events and activities! Thanks for your interest in becoming a part of the Graduate Health Network, we'll see you soon!

organizations.name: American College of Healthcare Executives at UCF
organizations.description: The mission of the American College of Healthcare Executives at UCF is to support students to achieve their professional goals related to Healthcare Executive positions and being the official intermediaries between ACHE nationwide and UCF.  ACHE is a national organization with multiple independent chapters in each state and subsequent region. Our nearest chapter is the Central Florida chapter. You can be a part of this chapter as a student associate, and this is open to all students from different universities in the surrounding areas. However, as a UCF student, you have exclusive access to ACHE at UCF which supplements the diverse benefits you get as a student associate. As a UCF student, you can leverage dual membership to experience additional events and opportunities in addition to ACHE Student Associate membership.

organizations.name: Lambda Theta Phi Latin Fraternity, Inc.
organizations.description: The mission of Lambda Theta Phi is to empower the Latin male through scholarship, Brotherhood, opportunity and protection of identity and equality. IDEALS 1. To establish a brotherhood 2. To establish and maintain a high standard of learning 3. To raise the standards of morality and develop character 4. To respect culture and practice chivalry 5. To promote the spirit of man's dignity and self-identity

organizations.name: Men's Lacrosse Club @ UCF
organizations.description: Lacrosse

organizations.name: Knights For Initiatives in Robotic Student Teaching
organizations.description: Mission The mission of Knights For Initiatives in Robotic Student Teaching is to connect students interested in youth robotics programs with opportunities to volunteer with organizations in the Orlando community, network with professionals in the field, and interact with a community of like-minded students. Goals We hope to collect a pool of UCF students interested in providing youth with a skill development opportunity through robotics, utilize those members to advance the quality of youth robotics programs in the area, and inspire the next generation of the workforce through a wholesome, hands-on experience. We aim to improve the UCF community through service that will improve the greater Orlando community.

organizations.name: Chabad Jewish Student Group
organizations.description: With the vision to open the door of Judaism to all  students and faculty on the UCF campus, we have established The Chabad House, a place where Jews of all backgrounds and degrees of observance can enjoy exploring their Jewish heritage in a warm, welcoming and non-judgmental environment.  We focus on traditional Jewish values through the perspective of Chasidic philosophy. Our programs include but are not limited to: weekly Shabbat dinners and services, Weekly BBQ's holiday programs, social activities, and classes. with both an active student organization and Jewish chaplain, Chabad is committed to try and reach every Jew.

organizations.name: Turning Point USA
organizations.description: Through non-partisan debate, dialogue, and discussion, Turning Point USA believes that every young person can be enlightened to true free market values.

organizations.name: REN Knights
organizations.description: "Huzzah, and welcome to the realm!" REN Knights is UCF's home for all things Renaissance! Whether you're a history lover, fantasy nerd, theater kid, DnD devotee, or just someone who thinks chainmail is cool‚Äîwe've got a seat at the table (right next to the bard). Our mission is to celebrate the spirit of the Renaissance through immersive, themed events and to find ways for students to experience renaissance fairs for themselves. We strive to build an inclusive community where you can explore, create, perform, and connect‚Äîno crown required. Join our discord and follow our instagram to stay connected!

organizations.name: Mediation Team
organizations.description: Students will learn the process of Mediation, learn how to deliver a mediator's opening statement, work with and be part of a team atmosphere, learn how to solve issues between parties constructively according to the law.   Interested in Joining? Please email sa746701@ucf.edu or christy.foley@ucf.edu for more information.

organizations.name: Knights Disc Golf Club
organizations.description: We are Knights Disc Golf! Want to learn one of the fastest growing sports in the world? Want to make new friends? We want to see you!  Disc Golf is exactly how it sounds: golf with frisbees. But, it so much more than that - the opportunity to represent UCF on the college circuit, improve your skills, and get outside with friends.  Come find us on Discord:

organizations.name: Aspect Dance Team
organizations.description: Aspect Dance Team is a group dedicated to covering choreography from popular Korean media. Members will gain proficiency in all aspects of a dance production by performing live and uploading filmed and edited dances to various social media platforms. Members will also get the unique opportunity to coordinate stage costumes with their peers to contribute to the visual aspect of the choreography. Participants will also gain skills relating to teamwork and sportsmanship by collaborating with their peers in practices and performances.

organizations.name: Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Power and Energy Society at the University of Central Florida
organizations.description: IEEE PES UCF provides the world's largest forum for sharing the latest in technological developments in the electric power industry, for developing standards that guide the development and construction of equipment and systems, and for educating members of the industry and the general public. Contact us: ucf.ieee.pes@gmail.com Or on our socials: Discord: https://discord.gg/PPVqUJNS9M Instagram: ieeepes.ucf

organizations.name: International Medical Outreach
organizations.description: International Medical Outreach (IMO) is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit that is dedicated to the provision of service and education to underserved communities across the globe. Through efforts in education and volunteering, our mission hopes not only to improve upon the sustainability and efficacy of medical care in the areas we serve, but to instill in our members an ethos of multiculturalism and medical altruism that shall continue throughout their lives. By means of our members and mission, we hope to leave a lasting legacy of medical care, service, and compassion within all of the areas we serve. Four times a year, our members have the opportunity to serve as part of a team on medical volunteer trips to various countries. On these trips, we are able to provide free medical care through the setup of pop-up clinics, aid in educating for children of the communities we serve, run donation drives, and develop presentations on health education to address the needs of the community. Our members provide assistance to physicians and other allied health professionals in both rural and urban clinics. Our efforts span over various underserved communities in Haiti, India, Colombia, PeruÃÅ, Brazil, and Puerto Rico; where we have fortunately witnessed positive change on numerous accounts.  Please email president@imoucf.org for more information!

organizations.name: Knights Kangna
organizations.description: The University of Central Florida's competitive and non-competitive Bollywood fusion dance team that aims to spread American and Indian dance culture by performing at competitions and campus events.

organizations.name: The Biomedical Engineering Society at UCF
organizations.description: The mission of the Biomedical Engineering Society at UCF is to build and support the biomedical engineering community locally, nationally and internationally, with activities designed to communicate recent advances, discoveries, and inventions; promote education and professional development; and integrate the perspectives of the academic, engineering and medical fields.  Join our Discord for updates! -> https://discord.gg/Bpkz8RyKg3 <-

organizations.name: Society of Women in Space Exploration
organizations.description: The mission of Society of Women in Space Exploration is to promote and encourage a stronger female presence in multidisciplinary fields of space exploration. We aim to create an environment where anyone can come and feel not only invited but supported as well. We hope to create the next female leaders in the space industry through networking and creating a support system for everyone in SWISE.

organizations.name: Esports at UCF
organizations.description: At Esports at UCF we have the following goals: To create a professional environment for student competitors. Currently, the most successful business model in the world of esports is the Esports Organization. This is what we will try to model ourselves after unless a better format is discovered. We aim to include and support teams across a variety of competitive video game titles, and promote professionalism and ethical conduct amongst our members. To create an inclusive environment for everyone. We will include and support community members of all backgrounds and skill levels. We make sure to provide a variety of events and opportunities in order to keep people engaged and involved no matter what they joined the community for. To establish a brand. We will promote our program, our teams, our events, and our community using every method available to us. This will include social media, securing sponsors, and improving our standing within the school. To grow the competitive gaming community at UCF. We are aware that there are many students here at UCF who are interested in esports in some way, whether they are looking to become involved as a player, coach, manager, photographer, or simply an avid fan. We will become the hub for the esports community here at UCF, giving all interested students a place to come together and develop their skills and build relationships. Click here to get involved!

organizations.name: Quotes, the Ad/PR Club at UCF
organizations.description: Welcome to Quotes, the Advertising and Public Relations Club at the University of Central Florida. Quotes is the local student chapter of FPRA, the Florida Public Relations Association. The value of public relations is essential across all industries and all fields. Whether you're an advertising and public relations major, a business-related major or even a pre-health major, joining Quotes offers an incredible opportunity for professional development, networking and understanding of public relations for every student. Quotes serves as the link between your role as a student and your role beyond graduation. The organization provides the unique opportunity to learn more about the profession, make new connections and stay in touch with local practitioners. Through teamwork and collaboration, the entire executive board has volunteered its time to make this a successful year and looks forward to fostering our shared endeavors.

organizations.name: Hearts for the Homeless Orlando
organizations.description: Hearts for the Homeless Orlando seeks to contribute to the health and well-being of one of the most vulnerable populations in our nation through free blood pressure screening opportunities, general education, and outreach opportunities. Please direct all inquires and interest through our listed email

organizations.name: Kendo Club @ UCF
organizations.description: Kendo, meaning "Way of The Sword", is a modern Japanese martial art of sword-fighting based on traditional samurai swordsmanship, or kenjutsu. Kendo is a physically and mentally challenging activity that combines strong martial arts values with sport-like physical elements.   Practice times for Spring 2025: Practices begin Tuesday, January 21st Tuesday/Thursday 9:30pm-11:30pm Sunday 1:00-3:00pm     Practice will be held in the Group Exercise Studio 2 in the RWC (main gym).   This room is located on the bottom floor of the RWC near the indoor basketball/volleyball courts. Wear clothes that are easy to move in and breathable, or if you have hakama and gi make sure you wear it to every practice. Please show up at least 15 minutes early so you can change and practice can start on time. Make sure you eat and drink plenty of water before practice. Can't wait to see you all there!   Please sign up on IMLeagues  and complete the Sport Club Acknowledgement Statement and Concussion Policy before attending the first practice.     Feel free to join our club's discord server to stay up to date:  https://discord.gg/4dTsMTzZT8

organizations.name: Survivor UCF
organizations.description: Survivor UCF is a group of students and fans of the CBS Reality TV Series Survivor , dedicated to running our own version of the game on UCF Campus, as well as hosting watch parties.   With a goal of hosting at least two per semester, the primary function of Survivor UCF is to host our own seasons of the game where UCF students can outwit, outplay, and outlast the competition until only one remains.   Just like on the show, we have our own custom-designed and manufactured Buffs that players in the season will get to take home as memorabilia.  Each season has its own unique buff design, with varying colors to distinguish the opposing tribes.    Survivor UCF also will host weekly watch parties of CBS Survivor while it is airing.  The watch parties will be a space for fans of the show to watch the live airing of episodes, meet other fans, and discuss the events of the game.   Here are all of our links!

organizations.name: Association of Pre-Nursing Students
organizations.description: The mission of the College of Nursing at the University of Central Florida is to offer high-qual ity undergraduate and graduate academic programs designed to prepare nurses to practice in a continuously changing healthcare environment; to provide innovative access to education and research; to develop nurse clinicians, leaders and scholars who promote the health of diverse populations in local, national and global communities; and to touch lives, lead by example and make a difference through clinical excellence, research and community service.

organizations.name: Badminton Club @ UCF
organizations.description: Badminton Club is dedicated to students who either have a continuing interest in badminton or would like to unwind by trying a new sport. The club is open to anyone. Students who wish to come are free to play the sport with friends on their own or may ask any of the club board members for instructions and tips regarding the game. There is no need to worry about lack of ability; the students who have come to these meetings vary greatly in technical skill. We have all the equipment members need to play.  Please follow us on instagram "badminton_ucf" for practices date and time. We also post announcements on upcoming tournaments and activities.

organizations.name: National Residence Hall Honorary Pegasus Chapter
organizations.description: What is NRHH? NRHH is a national organization with chapters at college campuses across the United States. This organization is composed of on-campus individuals who value service, recognition, leadership, and academics. It is unique, in that it is the only honorary organization for students living in the residence halls and one of its main charges is to recognize those individuals who go above and beyond the call of duty to improve residence life programs through programming, community service, advocacy, and leadership development. NRHH is made up of both on and off-campus residents.   Interested in becoming a Diamond? Fill out this Interest Form and follow us on  Instagram   Of The Month Awards (OTMs) OTMs are "Of the Months" which are a way to recognize the amazing things going on at UCF. This recognition starts on the campus level and can possibly reach regional and national levels. Here's how to write the perfect OTM.   Committees NRHH Pegasus Chapter has four committees which focus on different areas. Committees are open to all students and meet bi-weekly.   See a description of each committee here.   Executive Board Director: Alexander Abraham  nrhhucf@gmail.com NRHH Representative: Allyson Myers  nrhhucf.rep@gmail.com Membership Coordinator: Sarah Howell  nrhhucf.membership@gmail.com Service Coordinator: Isabella Ferron  nrhhucf.service@gmail.com Recognition Coordinator: Cassandra Simmons  nrhhucf.recognition@gmail.com

organizations.name: Chargin' Knights
organizations.description: The Chargin' Knights Club is a community of students who are passionate about promoting sustainable transportation on campus and off campus. The club's main goal is to raise awareness about the benefits of using PEVs as a viable mode of transportation, while also emphasizing the importance of safety, maintenance, and environmental responsibility. The club hosts regular meetings and events where you can learn about the latest PEV technologies and safety practices, as well as participate in group rides with fellow members.   In addition, Chargin' Knights places a strong emphasis on environmental awareness and sustainability. By promoting the use of PEVs, the club aims to reduce carbon emissions and promote a cleaner, healthier environment. Members are encouraged to participate in community outreach programs and advocacy efforts to raise awareness about the environmental benefits of PEVs.   Finally, Chargin' Knights is dedicated to promoting proper maintenance and care of PEVs. Members are provided with resources on how to properly maintain their vehicles to ensure they operate in safe conditions and remain reliable for years to come.   Overall, Chargin' Knights is a welcoming community of students who share a passion for sustainable transportation, environmental responsibility, proper maintenance, safety, and group rides. Whether you're a seasoned PEV enthusiast or just starting to explore these vehicles, Chargin' Knights is a great place to connect with others who share similar interests and to learn more about the many benefits of using PEVs.

organizations.name: Turkish Students Association
organizations.description: The mission of the Turkish Student Association is to provide UCF students of Turkish descent to represent their Turkish identity within the UCF community and socialize. Our goal is to have Turkish Students of UCF feel at home and connect with their Turkish peers. This includes undergraduate students, graduate students, and faculty staff.

organizations.name: Anime Spot
organizations.description: This is the KnightConnect page for Anime Spot, the anime club at the University of Central Florida! We are one of the largest and longest-running Registered Student Organizations located at UCF! Here at Anime Spot, we hold a variety of events ranging from themed anime viewings to activity nights. We also host our own annual Cosplay Knights events, Day of Cosplay! Whether you are looking to find your next show to watch, make new friends, or just share your love for art and cosplay, we offer something for everyone. Our goal is not to just be another anime club, but to be a central hub for all anime and manga fans at UCF. We hope to see you at our next meeting!   Current Officers President: Daley Eisenmann Vice President: Sara Wise Secretary: Alondra Quezada Treasurer: Lorenzo Trocio Marketing: Kiera Friedman Cosplay Knights Director: Seth Malcolm Cosplay Knights Vice Director: Vic Schneider   Our most active platform is our Discord server; join to meet other anime fans at UCF! A-Spot Discord Server (Students/Alumni) Follow us on Instagram for announcements and up-to-date information on our events! A-Spot Instagram

organizations.name: Society for the Advancement of Minorities in STEM
organizations.description: SACNAS (Society for the Advancement of Chicanos/Native Americans in STEM) is a national organization with over 150 chapters in universities all over the country (as well as a national research conference every year), with the mission of encouraging more diversity within the STEM fields. Our goal is to foster a community of like-minded students, offer career development opportunities, as well as give back to the community through volunteering, and advocate for access to research, graduate school, and involvement in science and STEM. All students from all majors/disciplines are welcome to join us!   Here are some of the events and workshops we plan to do: - Workshops on graduate school and summer research programs application process - Applying for scholarships - How to get involved in research and find your field of interest - How to talk/write about your research - Why you should get involved in research, and/or go to graduate school

organizations.name: Lake Claire Apartments
organizations.description: To provide a residence life program that encourages a positive living and learning environment, supportive of students development in the college community by providing quality opportunities and connections for academic and personal growth.

organizations.name: Knights for Wildlife Conservation
organizations.description: Knights for Wildlife Conservation (KWC) inspires student involvement in conserving the habitats of wild animals and plant life through volunteer activities. By raising awareness in the community, we educate the general public of the dangers presented to both local and global environments. We strive to empower others to make an impact on the environment and their surrounding communities. We also share networking opportunities to prepare students for continued involvement upon graduation.    IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN BECOMING A MEMBER PLEASE EMAIL US AT kwcucf@gmail.com ! We will not accept your membership request until dues are paid! If you have paid dues and are still not accepted, please email us as well.  You can become a member at any time of the year. General Body meetings are open to interested students.

organizations.name: Pakistani Student Association
organizations.description: The Pakistani Student Association strives to celebrate, promote, and share the rich culture of Pakistan with the UCF student body through service-oriented, social, and educational events.

organizations.name: Student Veterans of America UCF Chapter
organizations.description: ***Veteran Knights*** The Student Veterans of America UCF Chapter is a student-led organization dedicated to supporting and empowering military veterans who are pursuing higher education at the University of Central Florida. Through community building, advocacy, and access to resources, the SVA UCF Chapter strives to create a welcoming and inclusive environment for all student veterans. The group provides a network of support for its members, helping them navigate their college experience, connect with local veteran organizations, and build lasting relationships with fellow student veterans. *** Our New Community Discord Page  ***

organizations.name: Bioethics Club
organizations.description: The Bioethics Club is a discussion-based organization. The purpose of this club is to allow students to explore and learn about the connection between ethics and scientific progress. During meetings, students will learn about and analyze various scientific scenarios, articles, hypotheticals, movie clips, etc. and be able to approach them from numerous different perspectives outside of their own. Our goal is to provide students with the ability to understand how morality differs (and why) from person to person, as well as provide them with the necessary processing abilities to navigate such difficult situations that they may encounter in their future careers.  The best place to keep up with/contact us is through our Instagram, thank you!

organizations.name: Knights Cricket Club
organizations.description: Mission The mission of Knights Cricket Club is to connect students who are interested in playing cricket and participate in cricket games with other colleges and local teams.   Goals The goals of Knights Cricket Club is to improve the existing abilities of each player and develop new skills. To work with athletes in attaining their individual goals. To encourage a strong work ethic. To encourage good sportsmanship and fair-play. To experience the excellent competition American College Cricket (ACC)

organizations.name: Psy-Squared - Sanford/Lake Mary
organizations.description: Psy-Squared is an organization aimed at the advancement and development of graduate students in the field of clinical psychology

organizations.name: Saudi Students Association
organizations.description: The Saudi Students Association (SSA) is a not-for-profit organization aim is to provide a space for Saudis students to share their culture with the UCF community (students, faculties, and staff). It intends to provide cultural awareness and understanding, and to enhance positive image about Saudi students. The Saudi Arabian Cultural Mission (SACM) is our main financial and academic sponsor at UCF. It help us address any concerns students might have as well as enhance the club growth to achieve the goals and benefits toward successful educational and career of students.

organizations.name: Theta Sigma Chapter of the International Fraternity of Delta Sigma Pi
organizations.description: Delta Sigma Pi is a professional fraternity organized to foster the study of business in universities; to encourage scholarship, social activity and the association of students for their mutual advancement by research and practice; to promote closer affiliation between the commercial world and students of commerce, and to further a higher standard of commercial ethics and culture and the civic and commercial welfare of the community.

organizations.name: Korean Culture Club
organizations.description: The Korean Culture Club (KCC) at UCF allows members to respectfully appreciate all aspects of Korean culture including but not limited to language, cuisine, music, dance, arts and history. Join our Discord . Follow us on Instagram . Follow our  Facebook page.

organizations.name: The Rosen Entrepreneurship & Innovation Club
organizations.description: Our Goals We aim to help you: ‚Ä¢ Cultivate an entrepreneurial mindset ‚Ä¢ Build career networks with Rosen College students and industry professionals ‚Ä¢ Access resources to create your own entrepreneurial ventures ‚Ä¢ Develop skills essential for success in hospitality and tourism entrepreneurship What We Offer REIgKNIGHTS hosts a variety of exciting opportunities, including: ‚Ä¢ Networking Events with industry leaders, entrepreneurs, and peers ‚Ä¢ Workshops and Seminars on business planning, marketing strategies, and financial management tailored to hospitality ‚Ä¢ Entrepreneurship Competitions where you can pitch innovative ideas, receive feedback from experts, and compete for awards and prizes ‚Ä¢ Collaboration Projects that let you tackle real-world challenges with local businesses and organizations ‚Ä¢ Membership Benefits including exclusive resources, mentorship opportunities, and industry insights Whether you're passionate about hospitality, marketing, leadership, or simply exploring your entrepreneurial side, REIgKNIGHTS welcomes students from all majors to join a vibrant community of innovators.

organizations.name: ToKnight Show
organizations.description: The mission of ToKnight Show is to teach students how to write and produce comedy sketches for the purpose of putting together a monthly variety show.

organizations.name: Knights of Distinction
organizations.description: Successful graduates are those who are able to make connections between experiences both inside and outside the classroom and to apply what they have learned to new contexts. The Knights of Distinction program is designed to help you do just that. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=932GSfG1RPI   The Knights of Distinction program is designed to help students connect the dots between their experiences inside the classroom and beyond. The program provides a framework for students to plan effectively; seek out meaningful, high-impact learning experiences; and leverage those experiences to prepare for what's next after UCF.   This program is designed to help students: ‚Ä¢Identify goals and craft individual plans to reach those goals ‚Ä¢Engage in meaningful, high-impact experiences such workshops, internships, study abroad, undergraduate research, service learning, etc. ‚Ä¢Reflect on how those experiences prepare them for the next stage of their careers after UCF ‚Ä¢Showcase their work and achievements by creating a final ePortfolio   Students who achieve Knight of Distinction will earn: ‚Ä¢ The formal "Knights of Distinction" designation on their transcripts ‚Ä¢ Completion letter from the Program Coordinator ‚Ä¢ A medallion to wear at graduation!   Visit our website for more information!   Apply today! We accept applications on a rolling basis.

organizations.name: Knights Pre-Law Association
organizations.description: Our club strives to gather pre-law students to form a supportive network of like minded individuals who wish to achieve a career in the law field. Our members have access to networking events to connect members with career focused individuals in the law profession. We help to connect students to internships, careers, and volunteer experience in the law field. Our members have access to LSAT preparation by their peers through group study sessions. We plan to have current or past Law students speak on their experiences with members so they have an idea what to expect in the coming years. We want to help members know their options post-graduate and have support from one another when applying to Law School. We also plan to hear from different speakers in the Law profession to allow students to figure out what exactly they would like to have as a career in the future, as well as allowing them to network.

organizations.name: The Affiliate Chapter of the National Black Association of Speech Language and Hearing at the University of Central Florida
organizations.description: The University of Central Florida chapter of NBASLH strive to connect members with the opportunity to build a community within one another, learn from each other, and expand on what we learn in the classroom. In this upcoming year we plan to expand the opportunities of members through informational general body meetings, guest speakers, campus involvement, community service, socials, etc. UCF's NBASLH wants to create an inclusive environment and use every opportunity to grow within our careers and ourselves. UCF NBASLH Membership Application

organizations.name: American Society of Mechanical Engineers
organizations.description: To become a member click here and to contact the officer team send an email to ucfasme@gmail.com We are the  American Society of Mechanical Engineers  student chapter at the  University of Central Florida .  ASME  is a national non-profit organization that enables skill development and career enrichment across all engineering disciplines. We encourage all majors to join and get involved! As a student organization at UCF, ASME helps students develop their professional and technical skills by offering access to a wide range of activities such as  projects, workshops, socials, tours, panels, and more!  If you would like to get involved and learn more about ASME, come out to the next General Body Meeting where all upcoming events and information about the club is announced!   For more information and membership sign ups please visit our website! http://www.asmeatucf.com/     Join our Discord to keep up to date with announcements and interact with the community! Discord   Follow us on social media to hear about upcoming events and meetings! Instagram

organizations.name: Students Who Care
organizations.description: The mission of Students Who Care is to connect undergraduate healthcare students nationwide with hospitalized children, isolated seniors, and their families, to provide fun, friendship and support. Our RSO provides monthly Ronald McDonald House volunteer opportunities, limited weekly volunteering at childrens hospitals, weekly volunteering at Somerby's senior facility, and fun socials. There is no shortage of volunteer hours we can provide you! Fill out the application linked below to join: https://docs.google.com/forms/ d/e/ 1FAIpQLSdYpQCTyrAwCR3Tmkvk3PrY FhI6AWIdv1_yqjjolbg4dhA0FA/ viewform

organizations.name: Mindful Readers Club
organizations.description: Hello Everyone! Mindful Readers Club is a club where individuals are able to feel themselves and learn about psychology through literature, as well as make friendships for the rest of their college career. We focus on reading books that have to do with different disorders. We would dissect them together and be able to come together as a community to be able to have fun while learning psychological disorders and their symptoms, and how other interpret the books. We would also have activities like making bookmarks, collaborating with our local library, having blind dates with books, and movie nights! Follow our Instagram to stay updated with new events and activities!

organizations.name: Rosen Life
organizations.description: Rosen Life strives to further the sense of UCF spirit and community at the Rosen College campus. This includes, but is not limited to, surveying student opinions, advocating for Rosen College student needs, representing Rosen College students to Student Government, and by providing diverse and unique events for the UCF student body! We are funded through the Activity and Service Fee, allocated to Rosen Life through Student Government and the Office of Student Involvement. Each of our eight (8) directors are responsible for the execution of a specific type of events relating to Rosen Life's mission. The overall function and direction of the organization are managed by the Student Director and Assistant Student Director of Rosen life. organizations.name: Students for the Exploration and Development of Space
organizations.description: The Students for the Exploration and Development of Space (SEDS) is non-profit student-run organization that empowers young people to participate and make an impact in space exploration. SEDS helps students develop their technical and leadership skills by providing opportunities to manage and participate in national projects, attend conferences, publish their work, and develop their professional network, in order to help students become more effective in their present and future careers in industry, academia, government, and education. Our belief is that focusing on the enthusiasm of young people is the key to our future in space and to important breakthroughs in science and technology. Email us (contact@sedsucf.org), visit our website , or join the discord server for more information on how to become a member!

organizations.name: Project Downtown Orlando at UCF
organizations.description: The mission of PROJECT DOWNTOWN ORLANDO AT UCF is to contribute to the well-being of the greater Orlando community by providing necessary services to the homeless, indigent, and disadvantaged communities. organizations.name: Japanese Heritage Student Association
