organizations.description: https://youtube.com/channel/UC2H2rUO1qtr1I5YzSTVpFBg

organizations.name: SISTUHS, Inc. at UCF
organizations.description: SISTUHS, Incorporated is an organization for women that was established to foster an environment conducive to learning about the history and role women of color have in this society; develop local leadership to respond to the community needs, particularly those of women. Our mission is to improve the social disposition of underrepresented populations through community service, education, and other social services in our respective communities.

organizations.name: Institute of Electrical and Electronic Engineers at UCF
organizations.description: IEEE UCF  is committed to advancing technology for the betterment of humanity. Our mission is to empower our members by fostering growth in engineering, computer science, professionalism, and community service.   Check out our website! To get involved and stay informed about upcoming events, be sure to join our Discord community:  Join our Discord   We offer a diverse range of technical workshops , covering everything from fundamental skills like soldering, microcontroller programming, and breadboarding, to advanced topics such as RISC-V computer architecture. These hands-on experiences are designed to equip students with the knowledge and confidence to excel in their fields.   At IEEE UCF, we continually challenge the limits of what student engineers can achieve, creating an environment where innovation and collaboration thrive. This year, we will be having eight  unique projects that not only provide an enjoyable experience for our members but also significantly enhance their resumes.

organizations.name: Indian Student Association
organizations.description: The Indian Student Association (ISA), a non-profit organization at the University of Central Florida, was established in 1995 with the goals and ideals of preserving and spreading the rich traditions and cultures of India. The Indian Student Association hosts a multitude of major events- such as Garba, Diwali, and Holi- and general body meetings (GBMs) to educate students at the University of Central Florida and the community about the unique cultures and practices of India.    The mission of the Indian Student Association is to promote the cultures and social well-being of Indian- American students, international Indian students, and the Asian- American communities at the University of Central Florida.

organizations.name: Knights Rock Band
organizations.description: Knights Rock Band is a student-led organization dedicated to bringing musicians and music lovers together to jam, perform, and connect with the local music scene. We provide a welcoming space for musicians of all skill levels to gain real band experience, collaborate with others, and improve their musical abilities while also helping listeners engage with live music culture. Club Goals & Efforts Facilitating Live Music Collaboration ‚Äì We host jam sessions, open mics, and band meetups to allow musicians to play together in a relaxed, supportive setting. Developing Performance Experience ‚Äì Our club organizes live music events where members can showcase their talent on stage. Encouraging Band Formation & Promotion ‚Äì Creating a system to help students find bandmates, experiment with different genres, and gain exposure through performance opportunities and club promotions. Fostering a Social & Supportive Community ‚Äì Our events are designed to connect musicians, listeners, and music lovers through shared live music experiences. Connecting Members to the Music Scene ‚Äì We arrange group outings to concerts, local venues, and festivals to help members engage with Orlando's live music culture. Providing Hands-On Skill Development ‚Äì Developing workshops that emphasize playing together, refining techniques, and learning through experience. Exploring Multiple Genres ‚Äì While rooted in rock, we embrace a diverse range of styles, including funk, blues, alternative, and more. With regular events, club resources, and a strong community of musicians and listeners, Knights Rock Band is the perfect place to grow as a performer, build connections, and enjoy live music .

organizations.name: Politics, Philosophy, and Economics at UCF
organizations.description: The mission of PPE at UCF is to foster interdisciplinary study in the fields of Politics, Philosophy, and Economics; facilitate educated discourse in these areas; and develop the collective capacity to reason critically.

organizations.name: Delight at UCF
organizations.description: Inviting college women into a Christ-centered community that fosters vulnerability and transforms stories. Stay tuned on social media for meeting times and community events! join our GroupMe! https://groupme.com/join_group/63334543/1UL0KUsN Mission   Delight seeks to establish a college community that grows together, serves together, learns together, and does life together while chasing the heart of God. Delight is intentional about learning from one another through stories and experiences while potentially discovering or continuing to grow in relationships with Christ. Goals Delight exists to be a place that any UCF collegiate woman can come and grow in relationships with others, ask difficult questions, and find a strong community of Christians and non-Christians alike. Delight provides an opportunity for the students of UCF to explore their faith in a nonjudgmental and open environment.

organizations.name: Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers - Engineering in Medicine and Biology Society at UCF
organizations.description: Who We Are Welcome to IEEE EMBS at UCF! We're the University of Central Florida's student chapter of the global IEEE Engineering in Medicine and Biology Society. Our community explores the intersection of engineering and healthcare, inspiring and empowering the next generation of biomedical innovators. What We Do At EMBS UCF, we offer a dynamic environment for students to dive into the vast and impactful field of biomedical engineering. Here's a glimpse of what we offer: Projects : Oxygen Concentrator Build! This fall, we're kicking off an exciting project to build a functional oxygen concentrator, providing hands-on experience in medical device design and development. Workshops : Gain practical skills with workshops covering topics like CFD (Computational Fluid Dynamics), MATLAB, Machine Learning, and biosensors . Guest Speakers & Networking : Hear from leading professionals and connect with faculty, alumni, and industry leaders to explore career paths and opportunities. Community : Join a supportive and engaging group of students who share your drive and curiosity. Who Should Join? Anyone and everyone with a passion for innovation in healthcare! We welcome students from all majors‚Äîincluding Mechanical Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, Biology, Pre-Med, and more. If you're curious about how engineering can transform medicine and improve lives, EMBS UCF is the place for you. Why Join Us? Your time at UCF is a unique opportunity to shape your future. EMBS UCF offers you a platform to explore your passion, gain practical skills, expand your network, and make a difference in the healthcare field. Join our Discord!

organizations.name: Ballroom Knights
organizations.description: Ballroom Knights is a dance organization at UCF that aims to share the experience of ballroom dance. We welcome people from all levels to come together and simply enjoy dancing! No prior experience or partner necessary! Our classes and socials are free to all UCF students, where we teach and dance various styles such as Cha Cha and Waltz. We offer opportunities to dance in the Orlando community with organizations like USA Dance. Additionally, we offer a novice performance team and competitive opportunities. Follow us on Instagram or join our Discord server to stay updated! Discord Link:  https://discord.gg/BEfh98

organizations.name: Student Athletic Trainers Organization
organizations.description: Students seeking information on the Master of Athletic Training (MAT) program at UCF can visit the program's website at https://healthprofessions.ucf.edu/athletictraining/

organizations.name: Men's Volleyball Club at UCF
organizations.description: The Men's Volleyball Club at UCF is a competitive volleyball team that competes in both local and nationwide tournaments.  The club practices three times a week and participates in other activities outside of volleyball such as community service events and fun socials. We normally have 3-4 teams per semester, A team being composed of the most skilled players, B team being the next best team, and then C team is normally a developmental team where players learn the skills to move up to our A and B teams. Over the past 10 years, our A team has consistently been ranked within the top 25 teams in the nation at the end of each year by NCVF. In this past season 2023-2024, as well as the 2019-2020, A team battled their way to the highest ranking in our team's history, 2nd in the entire nation according to NCVF rankings. Our A team not only won 1st place in the Silver Division I at the NCVF, but they also went undefeated and won first in the 2024 ECVA Division I Championship. 2024-2025's B team finished 3rd place overall in D3AA at nationals in Phoenix, Arizona, placing the highest in B team's history. We hope to compete and bring home more podium finishes at Kansas City in 2026!

organizations.name: Computer Hardware Innovation and Design Association
organizations.description: Mission Our mission is to provide academic support to all students in the Computer Architecture domain in order to hone their technical expertise to gain leadership experience, develop projects, network with other computer engineers, including students, faculty and professionals, and start building their resume. The organization provides programs that encourage academic excellence, innovation and personal growth by providing students with the tools, resources, guidance and inspiration to build their own future in the field of computer architecture. Goals Our goal is to provide UCF computer engineering, electrical engineering students and any students interested in computer hardware with development opportunities and leadership experiences through project development and networking at numerous conferences. Connect via Discord group chat: CHIDA

organizations.name: Jet and Aeronautics Society at UCF
organizations.description: JAS is a society of engineering students at the University of Central Florida, dedicated to providing a new way of receiving hands on education through technical projects, focusing on jet propulsion & Aeronautics

organizations.name: Society of Professional Journalists
organizations.description: The Society of Professional Journalists chapter for the University of Central Florida. We promote being honest, truth-seeking journalists and encourage students to go above and beyond in journalism.

organizations.name: Women‚Äôs Pre-Dental Association
organizations.description: The mission of Women's Pre-Dental Association is to empower women pursuing dentistry by providing educational resources, career development opportunities, and resume enhancement to support their journey toward dental school. Our goals are to create  an environment where women can gain knowledge and confidence in their careers in dentistry by building a supportive network of dental professionals who share their personal experiences and insights into the field. Promote diversity within dentistry and advocate for equitable opportunities for women while encouraging professional and personal development through mentorship, workshops, and leadership opportunities. Provide engaging workshops that prepare members for dental school applications, interviews, and the Dental Admission Test. Facilitate networking and connections with dental professionals, alumni, and current dental students to foster relationships and career growth. Additionally, encourage members to take on leadership positions to further develop their skills and influence within the profession.   If you're interested in joining WPDA, following our Instagram account @UCFWPDA and join our flare chat! https://flare-event.app.link/OzTzjTl18Qb

organizations.name: Potter's Guild
organizations.description: Thank you for your interest in the UCF Potter's Guild. Our sponsored events are free and open to all UCF students. Membership is open to all students, non-art majors included, but the use of the facilities requires current enrollment in one of the 2000, 3000 or 4000 level ceramics courses. Members are subject to a guild fee to cover the cost of tools and materials.

organizations.name: Lebanese Student Association
organizations.description: The association is committed to benefiting the Lebanese, the non-Lebanese and the non-Arabic communities while promoting Lebanese culture and heritage, thus adding to the diversity of the campus, as well as increasing public awareness about Lebanese. We focus on promoting a sense of identity among Lebanese students, so as to portray a common image throughout UCF and creating an atmosphere for bettering academic performance and intellectual development of Lebanese students within UCF's community.

organizations.name: Doctoral Organization of Clinical Students in Psychology
Lambda Theta Alpha Latin Sorority, Inc.
organizations.description: "Latin by Tradition, Not by Definition" In the spring of 1999, after many years of trials and tribulations, 15 outstanding ladies established the Beta Theta Chapter. This made it the 31st chapter of Lambda Theta Alpha, the first Latin organization in the nation. Its purpose is to cater towards the needs of women on the UCF campus. Along with the accomplishment of the establishment of a chapter, the Founding Sisters of Beta Theta Chapter also established and fought for recognition of the Diversified Greek Council by the Greek community at UCF. This was a monumental accomplishment for Beta Theta chapter. Once the Diversified Greek Council was established and recognized, other multicultural Greek organizations were able to start a chapter on campus. On November 4, 2000, Line One was added to Beta Theta. This group of ladies had realized a long-standing goal of theirs when they were welcomed into the Lambda Theta Alpha sisterhood. Eventually, eleven ladies succeeded and became what is known as "The First Dynasty." From then on the legacy of Beta Theta continues to grow with high quality ladies that are determined to leave a mark on campus and in the community. Through various community service projects and educational programming, Beta Theta is making a difference. We are determined to give back, not only UCF but, the Central Florida community. Whether it is telethons with Arnold Palmer Hospital to help raise money for the cancer wing, or giving out food to the homeless, our sisterhood strives to help those in need. Beta Theta also does workshops on issues that can affect everyone, such as self-defense, as well as enlighten others on people and various walks of life. It is our hope to break down barriers within our community and to dissipate ignorance. We strive to become leaders and inspire other women to stand up for their beliefs and never stop reaching for their dreams. Mission:  The purpose of Lambda Theta Alpha shall be to provide a sisterhood based on Unity, Love, and Respect. To develop strong leaders who will then provide and practice political, social and cultural activities. Promote unity through charitable and educational programs. Maintain a higher standard of learning and serve as a voice for all students. Colors:  Burgundy and Grey Principles:  Unity, Love and Respect Goals:  Scholarly excellence, empowerment of Latinas and the universal woman, cultural and political awareness, and community activism. Important Facts: Founded at Kean University, in NJ in December of 1975. Lambda Theta Alpha was the first sorority ever created to cater towards the needs of Latinas in the nation. The purpose of the organization is to create a support group for women in higher education and unite the community on campus. Lambda Theta Alpha was established as an academic sorority. LTA is not an exclusionary organization. The LTA National Philanthropy is St. Jude Children's Research Hospital. Lambda Theta Alpha has a unique call, a hand-sign, and performs traditional salutes, chants, and strolls (party walks). Lambda Theta Alpha is a member of the National Association of Latino Fraternal Organizations (NALFO). Lambda Theta Alpha is a fully insured organization which covers all of its chapters. Lambda Theta Alpha has established Alumnae Chapters. Lambda Theta Alpha has established Graduate Chapters. Lambda Theta Alpha has established chapters throughout Arizona, California, Connecticut, Florida, Georgia, Idaho, Illinois, Maryland, Michigan, New Jersey, New Mexico, New York, North Carolina, Pennsylvania, Puerto Rico, Missouri, Texas, Virginia, Washington, Wisconsin, Delaware, Iowa, Tennessee, and Ohio Lambda Theta Alpha is proud to be recognized as the 2000-2001, 2002-2003, 2003-2004, and 2009-2010 recipient of the Sorority of the Year award from NALFO. Lambda Theta Alpha is proud to participate in the White House's Initiative on Educational Excellence for Hispanics

organizations.name: Knights of the Round Table
organizations.description: Knights of the RoundTable is an advisory council that serves as an educational and administrative resource to all student organizations and as a network between the organizations and the UCF community. We can help connect you to one of over 650 diverse registered student organizations on campus. If there is an organization we don't have that you want, we can help you start your own registered student organization!     2025 - 2026 Executive Board Executive Director ‚Äì Han Le | kort@ucf.edu Assistant Executive Director -  Hunter Layfield | kortad@ucf.edu Marketing & PR Coordinator - Juliette Rodrigue | kort_pr@ucf.edu Programming Coordinator  - Caelan Askew | kort_org@ucf.edu Programming Coordinator  - Anasofia Marin | kort_org2@ucf.edu Leadership Coordinator - Kai Hughes | kort_lc@ucf.edu   KnightQuest KnightQuest is a one-on-one consultation service that can help you get involved at UCF. We provide a personalized approach to your involvement through education on-campus resources that fit your personal needs or interests. Each consultation is designed to meet your individual interests regarding academic and campus resources, student organizations, and other opportunities. Schedule a Consultation:  https://calendly.com/kortoutreach KnightQuest Consultant - Trinity Burch | kortoutreach@ucf.edu KnightQuest Consultant - Rose Rodriguez | kortoutreach@ucf.edu   The Authorized Officer Webcourse for 2025-2026 is now available on the main page of KnightConnect!

organizations.name: First Person View Knights
organizations.description: The mission of First Person View Knights is to give UCF students a place to learn, design, and fly multi-rotor aircraft. We represent and place the University of Central Florida at the forefront of the Collegiate and Competitive Drone Racing scene. Goals: To introduce students to the realm of multi-rotors. To further the knowledge of those already in the hobby. To represent the University of Central Florida in the collegiate and general racing scene. Join our Discord for more information! Promotional Video

organizations.name: Figure Skating Recreational Club at UCF
organizations.description: The Figure Skating Club at UCF is designed to include all levels of skaters in the art and sport of figure skating. We strive to inspire students and help each other learn and grow creatively, athletically and socially in skating.

organizations.name: Association of Pre-Physician Assistants
organizations.description: Association of Pre Physician Associates (APPA) at the University of Central Florida is a student led organization focused on supporting and guiding aspiring Physician Associates as they complete undergraduate and graduate prerequisites. APPA fosters a collaborative environment where students grow academically, professionally, and personally while preparing for PA program admission. This organization provides access to essential resources such as guest speakers, including certified Physician Associates (PA-Cs) and current PA students, academic advising, informational workshops, and PA program profiles. Members also participate in service initiatives, fundraising, and volunteer opportunities to strengthen community engagement and professional development. In addition, APPA hosts fun social events throughout the year to help members unwind, build friendships, and enjoy being part of a supportive pre PA community. No matter your stage in the pre PA journey, whether you are curious about the PA profession or preparing for the GRE and applications, there is a place for you in APPA. Students interested in pursuing the PA profession are encouraged to join this network of motivated peers. Stay connected and updated on upcoming events by following us on Instagram: @appa_ucf .

organizations.name: Graduate Writers Association
organizations.description: The Graduate Writers' Association (GWA) helps students transition from the university setting to a literary and professional career in the field of English. We offer options for you to create and participate in networking and professional development opportunities and can help you establish connections by sharing our knowledge of national literary organizations and more. The GWA provides you with funding to travel to the annual Association for Writers & Writing Program (AWP) national conference (and an additional regional conference) and other opportunities such as reading at our monthly PARCELS event. If you contribute $20 for annual dues, you will be included in our conference funding and invited to special professional and extracurricular events. The GWA represents a great, accessible way of getting involved on campus and becoming a professional in the field of English. If you are interested in the GWA or have any questions about upcoming opportunities, we urge you to please contact the president at jordan.alexander@ucf.edu. Thank you so much‚Äîwe are greatly looking forward to serving you!

organizations.name: National Association of Black Accountants
organizations.description: Are you a student looking to advance your educational, professional, and personal goals? Do you want to network with top employers and explore valuable internship and job opportunities? If so, NABA UCF is the perfect organization for you! We welcome all majors and are a community of driven, ambitious students committed to helping one another grow. Our mission is to empower the next generation of leaders through mentorship, development, and opportunity. Together, we lift as we climb, and we want you to be a part of it. Join us and unlock your full potential. Hope to see you soon! Any Questions? Please email nabaucf@gmail.com or nabaucfvp@gmail.com

organizations.name: Combustion and Laser Diagnostics Society
organizations.description: The mission of the Combustion and Laser Diagnostics Society is to encourage and facilitate the UCF student participation in the science of combustion and optical diagnostics to raise awareness on combustion research for promoting a sustainable environment.

organizations.name: CREAR Futuros
organizations.description: CREAR Futuros, which means "To Create Futures" in Spanish, is a peer-mentor based initiative designed to improve Latino student success at UCF. CREAR (College REadiness, Achievement and Retention) Freshmen will be paired with knowledgeable and highly trained upper-classman UCF Peer-Mentors that will introduce them to campus resources and offer insight on how to make the most out of their UCF experience.   What are the benefits of joining? Join a National Network of Latino/a/x Leaders Receive 1-on-1 Support from a Peer Mentor Professional Development Opportunities A fun, cultural environment! What are mentee expectations? 1 year commitment Attend monthly virtual trainings Attend biweekly one-on-one Zooms with mentor Participate in monthly webinars Communicate with mentor on a weekly basis

organizations.name: Student Care Services
organizations.description: Student Care Services (SCS) offers guidance, resources, and referrals to UCF students who are experiencing a distressing situation which significantly impacts academic or personal success. The SCS team coordinates referrals to campus and community resources, develops action plans for student success, oversees the Student of Concern process, and provides education and outreach to university and community members. Our goal is to intervene before a student reaches crisis level and ensure the safety of both the student and the UCF community. SCS also oversees UCF Cares , an umbrella of care-related programs, resources and staff dedicated to fostering a caring community of Knights.

organizations.name: Association of Environmental Professionals at the University of Central Florida
organizations.description: The mission of the Association of Environmental Professionals at the University of Central Florida is to encourage members in the pursuit of environmentally related careers and to foster personal and professional development. Goals The goals are to provide an opportunity for members to become better informed on environmental issues of local interest and to provide a forum for encouraging and recognizing innovative, creative projects that address environmental concerns.  Goals also include the development of professional, networking relationships with other disciplines and professionals, including biology, planning, geology, engineering, landscape architecture, etc.   Join our discord: https://discord.gg/M8nebxhXyr Follow us on Instagram: aep.ucf Connect with us on LinkedIn:  https://www.linkedin.com/groups/12797348/ Join our GroupMe:  https://groupme.com/join_group/109882068/1F7Ucto8

organizations.name: Bangladeshi Student Association
organizations.description: The Bangladeshi Student Association at the University of Central Florida enables Bangladeshi/Bengali students to celebrate their language, traditions, and holidays, as well as creating a safe space to discuss the country's history.

organizations.name: Pre-Occupational Therapy Organization
organizations.description: The mission of Pre-Occupational Therapy Organization is to unite students interested in occupational therapy as a career while providing opportunities to be involved in this health community and gain knowledge and experience in the health care profession.    Here is the groupme for a better way to contact us and stay informed!  https://groupme.com/join_group/57294641/fuVIQxMT   2025-2026 Executive Board President: Mia Maccagnano Vice President: Isabella Ramirez  Treasurer: Brookelynn Bateman  Secretary: Kendrie Smith Volunteering Coordinator: Jordan Weintraub Social Media Coordinator: Olivia Hodgman Geer

organizations.name: Trial Team
organizations.description: At the start of each academic year, members of Trial Team get access to a complete criminal or civil case. This case comes with witness statements, affidavits, and evidence. We work in teams to develop ideas about how to best present this case to a jury (essentially, we do everything trial attorneys would do upon receiving a case). Some students play the role of attorneys and others play the role of witnesses. Throughout Fall and Spring semester, we travel across the country to compete in Mock Trial competitions against some of the best schools in the nation.  When you join Trial Team, you are coached by some of the most prominent attorneys in Orlando. These attorneys work to help you understand trial work, different areas of law, objections, presentation skills, etc.  You should consider joining Trial Team if ANY the following interest you: -Public Speaking -Competitive Settings -Leadership Opportunities -Team Environments  -Law School -Acting -Travel -Mentorship

organizations.name: Center for Community Partnerships
organizations.description: The Center for Community Partnerships develops, facilitates and supports university-community partnerships that strengthen communities in Central Florida. A major thrust of the center is to develop long-term partnerships between the College of Health and Public Affairs, other colleges across the University of Central Florida, and the Central Florida community.  The center focuses on the following areas: community engagement collaborative partnerships research and service long-term solutions to societal concerns At UCF, center personnel work closely with college administrators, department leaders and faculty members to identify critical community priorities, faculty interests and capabilities, and internal and external partnership opportunities. In the community, they place a priority on engaging community leaders, with several goals in mind: to develop strong interpersonal and inter-organizational relationships to develop a keen understanding of issues facing community members, schools, and government and nonprofit organizations in the public sector to facilitate discussions on strategies to address critical community concerns to initiate long-term partnerships to address those concerns The Center for Community Partnerships (CCP) strives to inspire students to play a role in the Orlando community through volunteerism. The CCP offers volunteer opportunities to UCF students at partnering organizations across the region.     These volunteer opportunities provide students with a chance to make impact on their community and themselves through the power of service. By being civically engaged, volunteers will learn important skills such as leadership and communication.

organizations.name: The Hypothesis Network
organizations.description: Our organization will pair students with research opportunities and shadowing opportunities at both UCF, online and other universities. We are having local lab managers come in and present on current exciting research, as well as recruit new RA's. We will create a database of recruiting labs as well as physicians allowing shadowing, which will vastly help students in their quest for graduate programs. We also have ample volunteering opportunities as well as seminars to help students get excited about any of the extra credit activate.

organizations.name: Men's Club Soccer @ UCF
organizations.description: Follow Out Instagram for questions and updates. @CLUBSOCCERUCF !!!   We are a competitive soccer team here at UCF. We mainly play against schools within the Southeastern United States as well as from across the country. The team has had much success in the last three years building a respectable reputation in the south east region. If you are interested in trying out for the team, please get in contact with one of our officers. We offer tryouts the second week of each spring and fall semester.

organizations.name: Phi Gamma Delta, International Fraternity
organizations.description: Phi Gamma Delta exists to promote lifelong friendships, to reaffirm high ethical standards and values, and to foster personal development in the pursuit of excellence. Phi Gamma Delta is committed to providing opportunities to each brother to develop responsibility, leadership, scholarship and social skills to become a fully contributing member of society.

organizations.name: Sanrio Appreciation Club
organizations.description: Hello! Welcome to the Sanrio Appreciation Club! The goal of our club is to make a welcoming community to promote positivity and de-stressing on campus. We aim to support each other with our mental health while taking part in relaxing activities and sharing our love of Sanrio. Feel free to join our Discord and socials to get announcements and recent news! Click Here for our Link Tree!

organizations.name: Fellowship of Christian Athletes
organizations.description: Our goals would be to establish Bible studies, or "huddles" that are available to all coaches and all athletes throughout UCF's sport programs (UCF Athletics, Club Sports, and Intramural Sports). We will do this by Engaging the hearts of coaches and athletes with the Good News of Jesus, the Christ, Equipping those coaches and athletes to do the same, and Empower them to lead others who will lead others!

organizations.name: Armwrestling at UCF
organizations.description: Arm wrestling club located at University of Central Florida! Stay updated through our discord and instagram page for upcoming events/meetings.  https://linktr.ee/armwrestlingatucf

organizations.name: WTS-UCF Knights Student Chapter
organizations.description: WTS at UCF aims to create professional college student community focusing on advancing women in transportation by offering scholarships, internships opportunities and networking events with the industry professionals. As a professional student club, our goal is to have a diverse team of students from different backgrounds to advance the world of transportation.

organizations.name: Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Inc.
organizations.description: To cultivate and encourage high scholastic and ethical standards, to promote unity and friendship among college women, to study and help alleviate problems concerning girls and women in order to improve their social stature, to maintain a progressive interest in college life, and to be of service to all mankind.

organizations.name: Flag Football Club at UCF
organizations.description: The flag football club provides opportunity for students to become more involved in the sport of flag football on the UCF Campus. We seek to teach students and athletes about the sport of flag football as well as provide a platform for those who played previously to continue playing. Members will be able to participate in practices, tournaments, social events, volunteering, and fundraising!

organizations.name: Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu
organizations.description: The Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu Club @ UCF is run like a traditional BJJ gym with recreational and instructional purpose. All levels of experience are welcome. There are no requirements to join. Practice is held at the RWC @ Ferrell Commons , next to the UCF LEAD Scholars Academy. If you face away from '63 South, it will be through the second set of doors.  As of Fall 2024, our schedule is Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, and Saturday--all 12:45-3:15pm. Please follow us on Instagram for the latest updates @bjjucf   Description of Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu: - Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu is a relatively new and constantly evolving sport that gained fame exponentially due to its effectiveness in mixed martial arts.  - Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu offers a fun alternative workout as well as a means to self-defense. - The sport holds therapeutic value, especially when it comes to dealing with stress and pressure. - It is often compared to chess as a mind game where the right know-how surpasses brute force.

organizations.name: National Association of Black Journalists
organizations.description: Mission Statement: To prepare, encourage, and educate minority students pursuing careers in the media. The mission of the National Association of Black Journalists is to act as a peer group of like-minded students working towards their personal and professional goals. The National Association of Black Journalists strives to help students with learning skills associated with the journalism major and provide them with information about professional development opportunities. The National Association of Black Journalists hopes to create a presence on campus for students who need to be surrounded by career-oriented individuals who are determined to have a job in the communication field post-graduation. In terms of our members, the organization wishes to give them as much information as possible before they join the workforce.

organizations.name: Student Nurses Association - Cocoa
organizations.description: Our goal is to facilitate the preparation of nursing students for assuming professional obligations. Also, to contribute to the holistic development of the individual and their accountability for healthcare delivery to diverse populations. Furthermore, to offer programs that reflect fundamental and contemporary professional interests and concerns.

organizations.name: Delta Tau Delta
organizations.description: Delta Tau Delta is rich in history. Founded in 1858 in what is now West Virginia, Delta Tau Delta has stood the test of time. It has survived two world wars, a Great Depression and a great recession, the boom of undergraduates brought on by the G.I. Bill, and the reduction of Fraternity membership following the Vietnam War. If you decide to join Delta Tau Delta, you can feel comfort in knowing that more than 150 years of history and tradition will be there to greet you.

organizations.name: Partners in Health ENGAGE@UCF
organizations.description: Partners in Health ENGAGE is a grassroots, student run organization that fights for global health equity and social justice. We are a part of a nation-wide network of other student organizations that work together to achieve our shared goal of global health equity. We organize a wide range of events including fundraisers for public health projects around the world, meetings with members of congress to advocate for global health legislation, and educational events to inform the community on issues relating to global health. If you are interested in joining our movement please reach our via the link below or contact our E-board! https://linktr.ee/pihe_ucf

organizations.name: ABC - Associated Builders & Contractors
organizations.description: Curious about construction?  Join us now and pave the way to a promising future in the industry! Explore the world of construction with ABC UCF ! As a UCF student organization, we are passionate about the construction industry and committed to preparing you for successful careers. Our offerings include: Project Site Tours Guest Speakers Networking Events Internship Opportunities Construction Management Competitions Leadership Positions Socials and Mixers And More!   Stay updated on all events and announcements by joining our discord. Visit our Linktree for Discord, Instagram, Social Media, Presentation slides, Calendar, and More! To officially become a member visit our ABC UCF Membership Payment Form:  https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScSn9pTCLgWe2dL1W3B2jRpHKZCLAbTjZWpE_96zUNy0sYXiQ/viewform

organizations.name: ForgetYouNot@UCF
organizations.description: Mission ForgetYouNot is dedicated to promoting community awareness about memory loss diseases, such as dementia and Alzhiemer's disease through presentations, volunteering, research opportunities, and community outreach. Purpose Through a variety of opportunities and activities like the Art Therapy Program, students gain valuable knowledge about memory loss diseases, connect with others, and engage in meaningful community outreach. ForgetYouNot provides an educational and safe space for patients to find strength in a community of people who understand their challenges. We also offer members hands-on volunteer experiences and the chance to make a positive impact on individuals affected by these conditions.

organizations.name: International Relations Club
organizations.description: The International Relations Club (IRC) focuses on providing members with academic and professional development for students at UCF. IRC's community helps one another learn about the various countries in the world, the greatest challenges facing international relations, and analyzes the future of international politics. Members are encouraged to ask questions, critically think about current events, and investigate why countries will do what they do and how to solve daunting challenges facing the world. Feel free to check out our social medias for club updates Instagram: @ucf.irc Discord Group  (https://discord.gg/dwb32Xjv23)

organizations.name: Beta Psi Omega Professional Biology Fraternity
organizations.shortName: BPO, BŒ®Œ©, or Beta Psi Omega
organizations.description: We are a co-ed professional fraternity dedicated to connecting people with a love for biology here at UCF. We are open to all majors, all you need is an interest in the biological sciences. We provide many leadership opportunities, as well as community service and research connections. Aside from professional development, we host many social events to help members build a supportive community on campus that is there for them not only in academics, but in life as well. Check us out & message us on Instagram! @bpoucf If you are interested in joining our fraternity, please come to our rush week events!

organizations.name: Mu Sigma Upsilon Sorority, Incorporated
organizations.description: Mu Sigma Upsilon Sorority, Incorporated was founded on November 21, 1981 as the first Multicultural sorority in the nation. This organization is comprised of women from various ethnic backgrounds, races, religions and creeds. The sisters of MSU share their culture and continually make efforts to educate society on those differences. This is the strength and core of their diverse sisterhood. They have a willingness to succeed, a sense of purpose to hold to their discipline of academic excellence and dedication to enrich the community.

organizations.name: Reel Knights
organizations.description: The UCF Fishing Club, The Reel Knights, have been UCF's fishing clu b since 2006. We are a devoted group of sportsman who enjoy the outdoors and just being on the water, while staying actively involved in the UCF and greater Central Florida communities. We have a lot to offer as a club from social aspects, in club tournaments, fishing gear, club kayaks, tackle discounts, and much more. MEMBERSHIP BENIFITS: As a member of the UCF Reel Knights you have the following benefits: Club t-shirt newly designed each year, access to all the clubs meetings and social events, priority entry into the clubs fishing tournaments, access to the clubs kayaks, discounted fishing gear from all our major sponsors, club raffles, club football tailgates, ability to be featured in our professionally-made production films, and lastly the club offers students the ability to make the large student body at UCF feel a little smaller and get to know other students with similar interests, go on fishing trips with each other, and much more. Members of the UCF Reel Knights also have the option to try out for the UCF Inshore Fishing Team and The UCF Bass Team each year. Our Mission: Preserving and promoting the sport of fishing at the University by giving students an opportunity to  share their passion with others in a structured, and comfortable atmosphere.      Contact Us at: UCF.reelknights@gmail.com Instagram: @UCF_ReelKnights

organizations.name: Society of Inclusion and Neurodiversity in Engineering
organizations.description: Hello! We are the Society of Inclusion and Neurodiversity in Engineering (aka SINE)! We are an Engineering/STEM RSO at the University of Central Florida! The mission of the Society of Inclusion and Neurodiversity in Engineering is to encourage all students students to achieve their greatest potential in the engineering industry. We strive to promote awareness of the neurodivergent experience, provide a community for neurodivergent students, and demonstrate the value of inclusion and diversity in engineering.

organizations.name: Central Florida Trumpet Guild
organizations.shortName: University of Central Florida Trumpet Guild

organizations.name: Knights Satellite Club
organizations.description: Knights Satellite Club is UCF's center for satellite and space systems development. We provide opportunities for students from all colleges who are passionate about space. Our primary focus is engineering and science, but all are welcome. It takes more than engineers to run a space program!   Projects KSC operates several projects to provide hands-on experience to our Members. We are currently developing two suborbital, balloon-based CubeSat test platforms that will fly up to 100,000 feet. We are also in the early phases of an orbital CubeSat mission. To communicate with these satellites, we are working on satellite ground stations on UCF's Engineering Building and Physical Science Building. We also build payloads for amateur rocketry projects in collaboration with other UCF RSOs.   Workshops KSC offers several workshops each semester. Leading up to career fairs and internship application periods, we hold professional development workshops to provide Members with valuable information and advice from recruiters and industry professionals.   Industry Tours and Conferences KSC partners with local Florida aerospace companies to offer industry tours giving Members valuable insights into their future career and direct connections for internship applications. We also provide opportunities to attend conferences such as the SmallSat Education Conference at Kennedy Space Center and the Small Satellite Conference in Salt Lake City, Utah.   Socials KSC holds socials throughout the year. In the past few semesters we have gone berry picking, played mini golf, gone tailgating, and visited Blaze Pizza, All My Tea Boba, and Fuzzy's Taco Shop. We are planning on more events such as paintball, bowling, and more restaurant visits.   How to Get Involved? We hold regular project meetings open to all students. The best way to get hands-on is to jump in and attend a project meeting! We also hold General Body Meetings (GBMs) once a month during the Fall and Spring semesters to provide general information and project updates to all KSC Members. GBMs also feature talks from industry professionals and free food! To stay up-to-date on events and projects, join our Discord !   Membership Steps To become an offical KSC Member and be eligible for all workshops, tours, conferences, and elections, follow the process below: 1. Complete Membership Form 2. Pay dues 3. Click join on our KnightConnect page   Leadership All KSC activities are student led and organized. Our leadership structure consists of elected Board Officers who serve for an entire year, and appointed Committee Chairs who serve single semester terms. Further leadership positions are available within Committees and Projects. These opportunities are open to all KSC Members who are excited about building UCF's student CubeSat program!

organizations.name: Institute of Industrial and Systems Engineers
organizations.description: The mission of the UCF Chapter of the Institute of Industrial & Systems Engineers is to support its members through continuing education, conferences, seminars, and networking activities to advance their knowledge base and empower them to influence positive changes in the industry. 2025-2026 Executive Board President: Carolina Estevez Vice President: Andres Flores Treasurer: Daniel Millan-Nieves Secretary: Mai Nguyen Chapter Advisor: Dr. Waldemar Karwowski (wkar@ucf.edu) Facebook Fan Page: https://www.facebook.com/iiseucf/ Instagram: @ucfiise Email: ucfiise@gmail.com Linktree:  https://linktr.ee/ucfiise

organizations.name: Women in Film
organizations.description: We host workshops, networking events, and guests speakers to educate members about women in film and the film industry. This club provides valuable opportunities for education and networking by supporting women and non-binary students as they navigate the film industry and work on student projects.

organizations.name: Pre-Student Osteopathic Medical Association
organizations.description: Pre-Soma is a student-led organization at UCF that aims to promote Osteopathic Medicine by building connections with members from all levels, including students and physicians. Our mission is to provide pre-medical students with access to meaningful experiences that foster academic growth, clinical exposure, leadership development, and service to the community. With this strong community, we can help our members gain all of the tools needed for professional school.

organizations.name: Criminal Justice Graduate Student Association
organizations.description: The Criminal Justice Graduate Student Association (CJGSA) is a student-led organization that is committed to the professional development of criminal justice graduate students at the University of Central Florida (UCF). The purpose of the organization is to promote the development of criminal justice graduate students in the areas of scholarship, teaching, and service. This organization is aimed specifically at criminal justice Ph.D. students at UCF. The organization will encourage empirical research related to criminal justice and criminology. The CJGSA will also enhance communication between faculty and students through hosting workshops aimed at improving teaching and research effectiveness. The organization's mission is to facilitate communication between criminal justice graduate students, criminal justice faculty, the College, the University, and community partners to maintain a network of colleagues in the criminal justice field. Members of the organization will also develop and preserve relationships with the community through volunteering and community outreach opportunities.  CJGSA membership is open to UCF criminal justice Ph.D. students only . However, the organization is committed to serving as a liaison between all criminal justice students and faculty at UCF. Some events hosted by the CJGSA will be open to criminal justice undergraduate and master's students in addition to Ph.D. students. Notifications about these events will be sent through students' UCF emails. If you have any questions regarding our association, please e-mail: cjgsaucf@gmail.com

organizations.name: Toys Kicking Cancer
organizations.description: Toys Kicking Cancer is a student-led philanthropic initiative created to bring joy to pediatric cancer patients during the holiday season. The organization collects new, unwrapped toys to donate to children undergoing cancer treatment, offering them moments of happiness and hope during a difficult time in their lives. Toys Kicking Cancer aims to kick cancer by delivering comfort and holiday spirit to young patients, ensuring they feel remembered, celebrated, and supported by their community. Anyone can contribute by donating toys or volunteering at events to help spread cheer and make a meaningful impact.

organizations.name: The Wetlands Club at UCF
organizations.description: The mission of The Wetlands Club is to build a community to promote understanding, conservation, protection, restoration, science-based management, and sustainability of wetlands. Join our GroupMe for updates https://groupme.com/join_group/104080683/HekpPl8p  We look forward to the 2025-2026 year!

organizations.name: Knights Nakshatra
organizations.description: Knights Nakshatra is UCF's premier Indian Classical dance team, dedicated to sharing the rich cultural heritage and beauty of Indian Classical dance. The team showcases a diverse repertoire, incorporating four classical dance forms: Bharatanatyam, known for its intricate footwork and expressive storytelling; Kathak, with its graceful spins and rhythmic footwork; Odissi, characterized by its fluid movements and sculpturesque poses; and Kuchipudi, renowned for its dynamic energy and dramatic expressions. Together, these styles create a vibrant and captivating performance that highlights the depth and diversity of Indian Classical dance.

organizations.name: American Sign Language Club
organizations.description: [To create a place for all students and those who seek knowledge and want to raise awareness of American Sign language, the Deaf Community, and Deaf Culture.] An exciting place to make new friends and practice American Sign Language and learn about Deaf Culture. we welcome beginner and advanced signers alike! Whether you are just learning your ABC's, or are a seasoned signer, we welcome YOU. The ASL Club mission is to create a place for all students, of all ages. We strive to create an exciting and fun environment where all people feel welcome, included, and important. We welcome hearing and Deaf alike, regardless of the person's level of competency in ASL. Our desire is not only to make a place for people to interact and make friends, but to shed light on, and raise awareness of Deaf Culture in our world today. We do this through the events we organize each year, which aid in connecting and unifying the hearing and Deaf communities. For more information concerning everything we are about, visit our Instagram page: @ASLKnights We look forward to learning with you, and creating exciting, enriching and unforgettable memories at the ASL Club @ UCF. GO ASL KNIGHTS! Past Guest appearances:  - Deaf Actor Ryan Lane from "Switched at Birth" - Deaf Comedian Richard Dahan - Deaf Actress Marlee Matlin - Deaf Actor, Winner of Dancing with the Stars and Americas next top model, Nyle DiMarco Past Events:  - Trip to Gallaudet University - Trip to FSDB  - FSDB Dance Troupe @ UCF   Join our discord to stay updated with the club at https://discord.gg/APawPwau

organizations.name: Volunteer UCF
organizations.description: Mission Volunteer UCF is dedicated to promoting civic engagement and education on various social topics to the UCF student body through educational and service projects. Purpose Through a variety of events and programs such as Knights Give Back and the Alternative Break Program, students gain valuable knowledge and experience, become connected to volunteer opportunities of their interest, and expand their community outreach. Volunteer UCF provides service event consultations and recognizes student volunteers for their outstanding service. We work with over 200 community organizations and continue to expand our agency's outreach.

organizations.name: Women's Ultimate Frisbee Club @ UCF
organizations.description: Welcome!!! to the Women's Ultimate Frisbee Sports Club at UCF (The Sirens) We pride ourselves in providing a competitive athletic environment while also growing friendships that will outlast the college years. We welcome any girl who is interested in joining, no experience, so come on out!   Absolutely no experience is required to join, we accept everyone onto our team with open arms!  For Fall 2025 starting on September 2nd our practices are: 5 - 8 pm Tuesdays at North Grass Fields (right near RWC park) 8 - 11 pm Thursdays at RWC Park Turf Field 6 If you have any questions, please don't hesitate to email us at ucfwultimate@gmail.com or reach out to us on social media! Instagram: sirens_ultimate    https://youtu.be/sKJeiHZIxOU

organizations.name: Real Estate Society
organizations.description: With regular meetings featuring guest speakers from all over the Central Florida real estate community, along with office visits and frequent internship opportunities, The UCF Real Estate Society is the place to be for those interested in real estate regardless of experience or major. Make sure you're following us on Instagram (@res_ucf), LinkedIn (The UCF Real Estate Society) & Facebook (UCF Real Estate Society) to stay up to date for meeting dates.

organizations.name: Health Awareness and Prevention Society
organizations.description: We are an organization open to all majors with the goal of promoting a healthy lifestyle for all students on campus! We provide lots of opportunities for members such as guest speakers who come in, volunteering opportunities, educational workshops, and many more. We provide a welcoming environment for everyone and would love to see you join us!

organizations.name: Student Government Legislative Branch (Senate)
organizations.description: The Student Body Senate is comprised of student leaders who represent the various Colleges and work with students and Registered Student Organizations . Our Student Body Senate provides students and organizations with the funds necessary for travel and conference registration, as well as campus-wide events and projects . Also, through various committees and caucuses, Senate has a great impact on issues that directly regard the Student Body. Student Senators also work on college-specific and/or campus-wide initiatives that better the student experience for UCF Knights!  Senate meets every Thursday evening at 7 :00 p.m.  It is encouraged that you attend these meetings so you can have a better understanding of your representative body as well as where your Activity and Service Fee is going. Over the summer, the Student Body Senate meets at 6 p.m.*

organizations.name: Sport Club Council
organizations.description: The University of Central Florida (UCF) Sport Club Council is an agency of the UCF Student Government Association (SGA) and is advised by the Sport Club Staff at the UCF Recreation & Wellness Center (RWC). Each Sport Club is a Registered Student Organization (RSO) with the Office of Student Involvement (OSI). Sport Clubs exist to promote and develop interest in a particular sport activity. Interests may be competitive, recreational, instructional or any combination of the three. Participation in Sport Clubs is strictly voluntary and membership is open to all currently enrolled UCF students who are paying the Activity & Service Fee. As RSO's, clubs are developed by students for students under the supervision of the Recreation & Wellness Center. The Sport Club staff of the RWC believes that involvement in the Sport Club Program enhances development, leadership, and the overall college experience for students by supplementing skills learned in the educational realm. It is the mission of the program to provide diverse sports opportunities for all students across a broad range of skill levels and experiences. organizations.name: Student Health Information Management Association
organizations.description: As of Fall 2025 to Spring 2026 Student Health Information Management Association at UCF Our Mission: To promote, educate, and represent the future of the HIM profession by creating educational events for our department's students and volunteering to contribute to our campus and community. Advisor:  Amanda Walden & Christine Neubert  President - Harika Malneedi Vice President - Nathan Woolson Secretary - Bailey Odvina Treasurer - Michael Kawa Social Chair- Demi Hoang    Applications  may be found in the documents tab OR on our website,  https://shimaatucf.wixsite.com/shima Thank you for your interest in our organization! Join us and enhance your HIM journey! We look forward to having you as new SHIMA members!

organizations.name: The Black Female Development Circle, Inc.
organizations.description: The Black Female Development Circle, Inc. at the University of Central Florida is a circle of women devoted to empowering each other throughout their college experience. Our three principles are Self Actualization and Improvement, Belief in a Higher Power, and Self Respect. Throughout the year, we host several events and socials that exemplify each of those principles. We provide leadership opportunities for our members in a fun, supportive environment.    The Black Female Development Circle is an organization of African American women that came together at the University of Florida in 1994. The group was founded to serve as a support system for black women. Meetings were to be a place where women with similar experiences could come together to discuss current events and find comfort from women who could relate to them. Since that time, collegiate chapters have been established at The University of Central Florida, University of South Florida, UConn, Flagler College, and the University of Miami.   Join our interest chat:  BFDC 25-26 Group Me

organizations.name: It Takes A Village
organizations.description: ITAV strives to provide community and resources for students, with a focus on non-traditional and transfer students who intend to pursue a graduate or professional degree. We work to stream-line resources and events that are useful to pre-grad/pre-professional students, and highlight research, volunteer, clinical, networking, and shadowing experiences for our members.

organizations.name: Collegiate Mathematical Society at UCF
organizations.description: Our goal is to provide opportunities including, but not limited to: 1) Intellectual activities such as problem solving competitions, guest speakers, forums, campus social activities. 2) Dissemination of information about internships, career opportunities, and graduate school. 3) Increasing communication and interaction between and among students and faculty. 4) Community projects that broaden the public's appreciation and understanding of the world of mathematics. 5) Contributing to the professional development of its membership by helping members attend conferences, encouraging members to conduct research, and assisting members with applying to REU's and graduate school.

organizations.name: Society of Optics Students
organizations.description: The mission of the Society of Optics Students is to uphold the principles of academic excellence, peer mentoring, leadership, and entrepreneurship to make an impact in the discipline of optics and photonics.  The purpose of this Chapter shall be the advancement and diffusion of knowledge of the science of optics/photonics and the encouragement of student interest in optics/photonics throughout the academic and local communities. Check the bio for link to discord. https://discord.gg/cQ3Z7w9HxK

organizations.name: Type 1
organizations.description: Registered Student Organization for students with Type 1 Diabetes at UCF. This club was created with the intention to pr ovide a relaxed and fun outlet to meet others with diabetes, interact with health care professionals , see and try new equipment, embrace new means to manage your health, and make new friends! The club is open to any students or faculty. You do not need to be Diabetic to join or get involved!

organizations.name: GenCLEO@UCF
organizations.description: Ready to turn your passion for the planet into real-world action? üåç Welcome to GenCLEO at UCF! As a part of the renowned CLEO Institute, we're more than just a club; we're a movement dedicated to tackling the climate crisis through education, advocacy, and engagement. We empower students like you to organize and take meaningful climate action by combining social justice with science, respecting the Earth's limited natural resources, and providing hands-on training. You'll get unique opportunities to work with community leaders, engage with local and state government, and collaborate with other GenCLEO branches to create a more sustainable and just community, right here on campus and across Florida. üíö Ready to be the change? Join our Discord and be part of the solution!   Join our Discord:  https://discord.gg/S4YBdXZM

organizations.name: Future Educators Association
organizations.description: Future Educators Association provides both professional development and social activities for individuals pursuing a career in education.

organizations.name: Kappa Kappa Psi Fraternity Eta Sigma
organizations.description: We, the brothers of Kappa Kappa Psi, believe that service to the college or university band program fosters responsibility, loyalty, and leadership; that a spirit of brotherhood is enhanced by the participation in a band program; that music is a universal language and truly the greatest of the arts; and that through fraternal participation, each member will strive for the highest.

organizations.name: Her Health
organizations.description: Her Health is an organization which aims to educate women about their reproductive health and rights, while promoting an inclusive space for all women. We attempt to de-stigmatize the talk surrounding women's sexual health by inviting speakers, such as gynecologists, and encouraging questions among participants in a judgement-free space. In addition, we give back to the community by hosting feminine hygiene product drives, and plan on partnering with like-minded RSOs on campus such as Period and PPGA.

organizations.name: OSI Productions
organizations.description: OSI Productions limits service to UCF departments outside of OSI, SG, SJA, and Pegasus Palooza in an effort to provide quality service to our internal areas. If seeking our services from outside the previously mentioned areas please email OSIProdirector@ucf.edu for further assistance. OSI Productions will not be reviewing forms during the following time periods: - Final Examination Periods  - Winter Break  - Spring Break Please note that during our busy seasons for OSI agencies, including Homecoming (October/November), UCFestival (March), and Knight-Thon (March), there may be delays in response to request from outside our agencies.   OSI Productions is a student-run production group funded by Student Government. As a team we work to provide high-quality video, photo, and livestream content to various departments and agencies across campus. If you wish to learn more about our organization, please feel free to send us an email at osiprodirector@ucf.edu For service requests scroll down to our forms section. To view form status and submissions follow these guidelines: click here . Re-submitting forms: click here .

organizations.name: We In Animation at UCF
organizations.description: We In Animation is the UCF chapter of the international organization, We in Animation (WIA). We are committed to celebrating and uplifting underrepresented and marginalized voices in the animation industry, while also providing professional development opportunities to our members. We welcome artists of all identities passionate about animation and more!   As a student organization affiliated with WIA, our goal is to bring together the global animation community to empower and advocate for people of underrepresented gender identities in the art, technology, production, and business of animation, inspiring excellence and justice in all facets of the industry.   The UCF collective works to achieve this by building a professional network, hosting talks and panels, and holding professional development workshops in cooperation with our parent organization.   Join us on KnightConnect and visit our website to learn more!

organizations.description: Mission The mission of PokéKnights is to create an environment that brings the many UCF students who love Pokémon together as one organization. Goals This organization focuses on the interest of Pokémon from all aspects, such as: Pokémon History Pokémon Anime Pokémon Video Games Pokémon Trading Card Game Pokémon Manga Pokémon GO Regular Club Meeting Information UCF PokeKnights Fall 2025 Main Campus In-Person Club Meetings Day: Wednesday Time: 7:00 PM - 8:45 PM Location: Student Union, Room 219 Social Media We use Discord to communicate! organizations.name: American Statistical Association at UCF
organizations.description: AmStat@UCF, a chapter of the American Statistical Association, provides a big tent for statistics within the University of Central Florida, forming a community of statisticians, data scientists, actuaries, and all who love statistics! Our chapter teaches members fundamental data science skills through workshops and gives opportunities to apply these skills with projects! Alongside having keynote speakers at our general body meetings and social events where our members can connect with other students, we aspire to make every member of our club better prepared for their careers, whether they go to graduate school or directly into industry or government.

organizations.description: To provide a residence life program that encourages a positive living and learning environment, supportive of students development in the college community by providing quality opportunities and connections for academic and personal growth.

organizations.name: Association for Computing Machinery
organizations.description: Official Computer / Programming club at UCF Join our Discord:  http://ucf.acm.org/discord Check out our linktr.ee ! The student chapter of an international organization focused on advancing the education and research in the field of Computer Science and Computer Engineering. Join the premiere organization in computing to gain leadership experience, participate in projects, network with other developers, professionals and start building your resume.

organizations.name: Orthodox Christian Campus Ministries
organizations.description: Orthodox Christian Campus Ministries organization aims to: Unify students together in Christ Be a part of the larger University of Central Florida community Help the Orlando community where help is needed Raise awareness of the Oriental Orthodox faith and church
