organizations.name: Undergraduate Physical Therapy Association
organizations.description: The Undergraduate Physical Therapy Association aims to provide a supportive network for students interested in physical therapy careers while providing them with information and opportunities necessary for admission into Doctor of Physical Therapy programs. Through the association, students will have the opportunity to meet practicing physical therapists, connect with volunteer experiences, participate in physical therapy events, learn about physical therapy graduate school requirements, and meet other students and faculty involved in physical therapy.  This page is relatively inactive, so join the  UPTA Facebook page  OR our Instagram ucf_upta in order to receive updates on upcoming events and get access to some exclusive free resources! You can officially join the club at anytime, just stop by one of our general body meetings! If you have any questions relating to the club, please email UPTAsecretary@gmail.com!

organizations.name: First Step
organizations.description: First Step aims to fight against the stigma that underclassmen (especially freshmen) are not suitable candidates to obtain an internship. Many underclassmen think that they are "not experienced enough" when in reality, they may have just as much experience or just as good of a resume as upperclassmen. First Step believes that underclassmen are capable of achieving such positions and are just as ready for such learning and technical applications as underclassmen are. It is the idea that the underclassmen have time to accomplish their goals that "justifies" them to wait until they are juniors or seniors to get internships/research experience that mentally blocks the first years from thinking that they can achieve greatness within their first year of university. Underclassmen have the capability of excelling in the industry as they stand.  First Step hopes to inspire and lead them to all of the opportunities that are available through an engineering and computer science mentorship program . Here, members are grouped with peer mentors who have obtained research and/or internship experience in their early undergraduate semesters.

organizations.name: Society of Themed Entertainment Engineers and Leaders
organizations.description: The Society of Themed Entertainment Engineers and Leaders is a brand new student organization that aims at propelling the professional development of its members within the realm of immersive experiences.  STEEL joins UCF's list of great themed entertainment clubs like FTPLA and TEA but sets itself apart by being the first CECS and Engineering Focused themed entertainment registered student organization.

organizations.name: Zeta Phi Beta Sorority, Incorporated
organizations.description: The Sophisticated Sigma Epsilon chapter graced the campus with its presence on April 5. 1978. Zeta Phi Beta Sorority, Inc. was founded on the principles of Service, Scholarship, Sisterly love, and Finer womanhood. We are a community conscious action-oriented sorority. Zeta women are not only hard working for Zeta but their talents are shared with organizations at UCF and in the Orlando community.

organizations.name: Sales Club of UCF
organizations.description: The Sales Club is an organization devoted to setting students up for success. The Sales Club promotes professional selling as a career, but also focuses on developing essential skills that are necessary to be successful no matter what career path you choose. Hence, this club welcomes students from all majors. Sales Club members are continuously improving their verbal communication skills in many fun and rewarding activities. As an active member you will practice and gain valuable knowledge on topics such as, networking, negotiating, business etiquette, public speaking, and body language. You will also learn how to sell your own talents and ideas when interviewing at your job, and in your everyday activities.

organizations.name: Towers I Apartments
organizations.description: To provide a residence life program that encourages a positive living and learning environment, supportive of students development in the college community by providing quality opportunities and connections for academic and personal growth.

organizations.name: Out in Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics at The University of Central Florida
organizations.description: We are Out in Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics at The University of Central Florida (oSTEM at UCF), a professional development organization focused on uniting students of STEM majors and LGBTQ+ identities. Our mission is to create and cultivate an environment where students at UCF, of all gender and sexual identities can unite, learn about various internship and employment opportunities, connect with a variety of professionals in STEM fields, and cultivate their personal and professional appearances to help maximize their success post-graduation. We are the local chapter of the national organization Out in Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics, and we are dedicated to continuing their work here at UCF.

organizations.name: Urban Knights Planning Association
organizations.description: The goals of this organization are to connect students, faculty and professionals to create networking for emerging urban planners. We network with planners all over Central Florida, providing advice, expertise, and career opportunities for Urban and Regional Planning students at the UCF Downtown Campus. This will create a mentor relationship between the students and planning professionals. We are involved in conferences, lecture series, and events that are taking place in Central Florida and encourage our members to attend these activities. Lastly, we seek to provide resources and activities for students currently engaged or interested in joining the UCF Urban Planning program.

organizations.name: Residence Hall Association
organizations.description: The Residence Hall Association, more commonly known as RHA, is a registered student organization that is affiliated with the Department of Housing and Residence Life (DHRL) and advised by a full-time DHRL professional staff member. RHA works year-round to bring the best opportunities to residents, and we strive to see them be actively involved in the community. RHA believes that through leadership, programming, and advocacy, our members can grow academically, professionally, and personally to have a more enriching university experience. RHA hosts events that are geared towards providing a fun experience for all on-campus residents. We provide funding to Area Councils in each community so they can do the same for residents across campus. Interested in joining RHA? Follow our Instagram (@rhaucf) and see how you can get involved!

organizations.name: Latinos In Action at University Of Central Florida College Chapter
Venezuelan Student Association
organizations.description: VENSA is dedicated to promoting the Venezuelan culture and heritage through social, professional, and charitable events. Our objective is to reach out and support Venezuelans within the UCF community, making sure everyone feels at home and helping each other thrive and succeed. Visit our Instagram for updates and reach out to join!!!

organizations.name: Christians on Campus
organizations.description: Christians on Campus is composed of students on campus who desire to give the Lord the first place and to build up a community on the UCF campus to give every student the opportunity to grow spiritually, gain life-long companions, and develop academically while in college. Christians on Campus has many chapters on many campuses throughout the nation but does not take direction from any central headquarters or organization. Instead, the members practice to fellowship with other clubs from the various campuses in semesterly gatherings and yearly conferences. Through the decades of the Christians on Campus ministry, many graduates are kept connected to the students from the campus where they graduated, and are easily plugged into another campus should they move to a new city for work or graduate school. These alumni are very useful in mentoring new students due to their previous experiences as students and their current professional development. Our goals are threefold: Our first goal is to cause the students to see how critical these college years are for their own pursuit of Christ, their education, and for their development in spirit, soul, and body. In addition, the club desires to produce many mentors who could carry on the care for the younger, incoming students coming to UCF. Secondly, our goal is to connect students with each other and with local Christian families and alumni throughout Central Florida and beyond to support the students in their spiritual condition, mental health, and academics. Finally, to equip all the students in the realization of the divine truths according to the Scriptures (2 Timothy 3:16-17, 1 Timothy 2:4, 2 Peter 3:18), and for each one to realize the application of the Scripture in their daily living.

organizations.name: D20 Knights
organizations.description: We are a tabletop gaming club at the University of Central Florida. We play an assortment of games - everything from RPGs to CCGs. Bring in your favorite board game or your deck of Magic cards and start a game! Or maybe you're looking for players to venture into your dungeons... What ever your reason, join us for some game time! Join us on our Discord (where most announcements are made and  where a good amount of groups are found )  https://discord.gg/yJSrqqT Or come find us on our Facebook group  https://www.facebook.com/groups/64015951332/

organizations.name: Libra Community
organizations.description: To provide a residence life program that encourages a positive living and learning environment, supportive of students development in the college community by providing quality opportunities and connections for academic and personal growth.

organizations.name: Women in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science
Black Student Union
organizations.description: We are the Black Student Union at the University of Central Florida. Our purpose is to serve as the official voice for the black community at the University. We have three goals for our organization, and they are:  To develop, implement, intensify, and perpetuate comprehensive programs. These programs will identify and deal with the problems of educational, political, and cultural dilemmas encountered by the UCF community with a focus on Black students while promoting a positive image of the Black culture to the university and outside communities. To establish and promote open lines of communication between the Black students and university administration, faculty, staff, and alumni in order to enhance the disseminating and receiving such information. To collaborate with other organizations to provide a diverse learning atmosphere to all UCF students. Founded on October 29, 1969, the Black Student Union was the first multicultural student organization on the University of Central Florida campus. We strive to create a home-away-from-home environment for all members, and to encourage students to become campus leaders. Make sure to follow us for all up to date information! Instagram: @bsu_ucf General Body Meetings Wednesdays @ 6pm

organizations.name: Planned Parenthood Generation Action
organizations.description: Planned Parenthood Generation Action at UCF exists to educate the university community about reproductive health and rights, to translate increased awareness in to reproductive justice activism on campus, and to serve as a coalition partner to state, national, and international reproductive justice efforts. 2025-2026 Membership Form

organizations.name: Robotics Club of Central Florida
organizations.description: About Us The Robotics Club of Central Florida is an entirely student-run organization. We focus on creating innovative and competitive robots in our lab. Our projects can involve demonstrations of robotics for community teaching, pushing the bounds of automation, and innovative, robust designs. We are always looking for dedicated people to join in the advancement of the demanding robotics field at any point in the process. We also always have workshops to help get members up to speed. Join Us Go to our website to become a member. Join our discord: Discord Email us: officers@rccf.club

organizations.name: Alpha Sigma Kappa - Women and Gender Minorities in Technical Studies
organizations.description: Mission Alpha Sigma Kappa - Women in Technical Studies¬Æ is a unique social sorority for women and non-binary people pursuing technical majors. Our sorority is composed of women and NBs who emphasize strong sisterly bonds with one another but also place importance on academics.We accept women/NBs in Engineering, Architecture, Mathematics, and the Sciences. While women/NBs have an ever-growing presence in these fields, we remain a minority in collegiate and professional arenas which can prove challenging. As a sorority, we offer women/NBs the opportunity to develop leadership skills, friendships, a sense of belonging, and a network of support. We encourage friendship - between you and your fellow sisters, fellowship - through shared interests, and commitment - to yourself, the organization, and your community. Support is essential while pursuing a degree in these technical fields because we all encounter the same challenges. A variety of activities is planned throughout the year for our members, including social, philanthropic, and scholastic events, to encourage a fun relaxed atmosphere without jeopardizing academics. Goals The purpose and goal of the Chapter to promote friendship, academic achievement, unity within the organization, women/NBs in technical fields, and philanthropy within the community.

organizations.name: Office of Research and Community Engagement
organizations.description: The Burnett Honors College has long been known for providing quality instruction in our classrooms and laboratories so that our Honors graduates are prepared for rich and productive lives in the workplace. We have now expanded our educational horizons so that our students are well educated for citizenship as well as for careers. One of the most important attributes of the UCF college experience is community engagement, which enhances one's personal and professional life. By serving others, students develop the ability to lead, to communicate effectively with diverse populations, and to understand complex issues within their community. Through the Honors Freshman Symposium, Elevation Fellows Program and the Honors Educational Reach Out (HERO) opportunities, the number of students who are interested in, excited about, and involved with community engagement at The Burnett Honors College has grown tremendously over the past five years. These opportunities provide students with a chance to contribute to their community, to take what they have learned in the classroom and the knowledge that they have acquired from their college experience and apply it for a greater good. By being engaged citizens, students not only make connections within the broader community, but also make connections within their respective student community. Being civically responsible affords students the chance to serve as leaders and mentors, communicate their shared interests and passions, and collaborate to change the way that future generations think about their livelihood.

organizations.name: Student Union
organizations.description: The Student Union is "The Heart of Campus" ; creating lasting first impressions by providing high quality facilities that are both student oriented and environmentally focused. We seek to enrich the student experience through innovative programming and civic engagement. We offer an experience based learning environment that fosters personal and professional growth. The Student Union consistently exceeds expectations by providing resourceful, courteous and attentive services in partnership with students, faculty, alumni, staff, parents and guests.

organizations.name: Harry Potter Club
organizations.description: When signing up,  please use your ucf.edu email only . We cannot invite emails ending with anything other than your school email. Thank you for your understanding and your patience!   Welcome to the Harry Potter Club!   Our main mission is to bring Hogwarts to the University of Central Florida. We are expecting to host a variety of events, such as a Sorting Ceremony, our own version of the Triwizard Tournament, movie/novel analyses, and even DIY wand and dragon egg sessions! If you would like to know more, send us an owl for more information.   discord:  https://discord.gg/d9AMq399yG

organizations.name: Pi Beta Phi Fraternity for Women
organizations.description: The vision of Pi Beta Phi Fraternity for Women is to be recognized as a premier organization for women by providing lifelong enrichment to its members and contributing to the betterment of society.

organizations.name: International Student Association
organizations.description: The International Student Association (ISA) is a diverse cultural entity at UCF. Our main mission is to unite all the diverse cultures around campus and promote awareness, understanding, and acceptance, while supporting international students as they get accustomed to the American life.  ISA serves as hub for social interaction and cultural events, networking, skill building, and as an academic resource where international students may come together and connect with UCF students both foreign and local. We not only embrace, but celebrate cultural traditions, allowing students to feel a sense of home here at UCF. Our goal is to promote togetherness, unity, friendship, and diversity.

organizations.name: Women's Volleyball Club at UCF
organizations.description: The Women's Volleyball Club at UCF, is a club for volleyball players with previous experience. Purpose: To play competitive volleyball without the extreme commitment of playing a regular college sport. Our goal is to play competitive volleyball while making great friends and memories. Our volleyball season starts at the beginning of fall and finishes at the end of the spring semester. General Info: Since we want everyone to be able to play, our club consists of two teams. We have practices a few times a week and have around 5 tournaments each semester. Travel: During fall we try to play other club teams in Florida. Some of the teams we have played in the past include University of Miami, University of Florida, University of South Florida, Florida State University, Stetson, etc. During spring semester we travel in and out of state to compete and be eligible to play at Nationals which is in Minneapolis, Minnesota in 2021. This past spring we traveled out of stated to play tournaments in North Carolina at UNC, Texas at University of Texas-Austin and Kansas City, Missouri for nationals. To stay informed please follow/like us on Facebook. All Club Volleyball events, practices, and open gyms will be announced there.

organizations.name: Institute of Transportation Engineers
organizations.description: The Institute of Transportation Engineers is an international educational and scientific association of transportation professionals who are responsible for meeting mobility and safety needs. The UCF student chapter holds meetings to bring in professional guest speakers, network with other students, and more. Please visit our  website  for all our information!

organizations.name: Emergency Medicine and Trauma Club
organizations.description: Welcome to EMTC - the Emergency Medicine and Trauma Club! Are you ready to dive into the high-octane world of emergency medicine and trauma care? If you're passionate about fast-paced decision-making, community involvement, and precision under pressure, then you've found your tribe! At EMTC, we're not just a club, we're a dynamic community of future medical professionals eager to explore the exhilarating realm of emergency medicine and trauma care. Here's what you can expect when you join us on this thrilling journey: High-Intensity Learning: Get ready for an adrenaline-fueled ride as we delve into the heart of emergency medicine. From rapid-fire decision-making scenarios to hands-on cadaver labs, we're committed to providing you with the real-world skills and knowledge you need to excel in this fast-paced field. Community Engagement: EMTC isn't just about mastering medical techniques; it's also about making a positive impact on the world around us. Through volunteering events and community outreach programs, we'll show you how to use your skills to give back and make a difference in the lives of others. Informative Sessions: Curious about different pathways into the medical field, including opportunities in the military? Our informational sessions will cover everything you need to know, from educational requirements to career options, so you can chart your course with confidence. Fun Exercises: Who says learning can't be fun? From interactive simulations to team-building activities, we believe in keeping things engaging and enjoyable as we explore the exciting world of emergency medicine and trauma care. Certifications: Want to boost your resume and expand your skill set? We've got you covered with opportunities to earn certifications that will set you apart as a future leader in the field. No Experience Required: Whether you're a certified health professional or just starting out on your journey, there's a place for you at EMTC. All you need is a strong work ethic, a passion for helping others, and a willingness to dive in headfirst. New Club, New Adventures: As a new club, we're still finding our footing, but we're excited to grow and evolve with each and every member. So come join us as we embark on this exciting new chapter together! Are you ready to unleash your inner hero and join us at EMTC? Come on out and discover the thrill of emergency medicine and trauma care with a community that's as passionate and dedicated as you are. We can't wait to welcome you aboard!   Join our GroupMe: https://groupme.com/join_group/97662475/URTa4w4t

organizations.name: Multicultural Student Center
organizations.description: The Multicultural Student Center (MSC) will help facilitate the inclusive shared learning experience for all UCF Knights. We will promote an environment that acknowledges respects, enhances, and celebrates all aspects of culture. Through intentional programming, with Student Organizations, and the UCF community, we will encourage the educational exploration of multiculturalism, engage in dialogue, challenge assumptions and barriers, and work with the surrounding community to support and build collaborative relationships across the University.

organizations.name: Bold Campus Ministry at UCF
organizations.description: Bold Campus Ministry is a dynamic and passionate Christian community dedicated to making a profound impact on college campuses across the nation. With an unapologetically bold approach to faith, this ministry seeks to empower students to live out their Christian values with confidence and conviction. At the heart of Bold Campus Ministry is a commitment to authentic relationships. The community is built on a foundation of genuine care, support, and accountability, creating a space where students can explore and deepen their faith in a welcoming and nonjudgmental environment. Worship gatherings with Bold Campus Ministry are characterized by lively and spirited expressions of faith. Through vibrant music, dynamic preaching, and engaging discussions, students are encouraged to encounter God in a way that is both meaningful and transformative. Bold Campus Ministry is not just about internal growth; it's about actively engaging with the world. The ministry is involved in various outreach initiatives, social justice causes, and community service projects. Through these efforts, students have the opportunity to tangibly express their faith by serving those in need and advocating for positive change in their communities. One of the distinctive features of Bold Campus Ministry is its emphasis on leadership development. Students are encouraged to step into leadership roles, empowering them to take ownership of their faith and become influential leaders on their campuses and beyond. In summary, Bold Campus Ministry is a vibrant and empowering Christian community that equips students to boldly live out their faith, engage with the world, and make a lasting impact on their college campuses. Through authentic relationships, dynamic worship, community outreach, and leadership development, this ministry strives to inspire a generation of confident and passionate followers of Christ.

organizations.name: Artificial Intelligence Club
organizations.description: AI@UCF offers a plethora of resources to help UCF students pursue interests in artificial intelligence, data science, and machine learning. We host introductory-level general body meetings, research paper discussions, and some project teams anyone can join to get hands-on experience. Anyone can join! No prior knowledge necessary.  Our community Discord server is the central hub for all of our communications. Click the link below to stay updated and connect with our members! Thank you :) JOIN HERE:  https://ucfai.org/discord

organizations.name: American Chemical Society
organizations.description: ACS at UCF provides a wide range of professional and academic development activities for our members.  We regularly host speakers on a wide array of chemistry-related topics, including professors and industry spokespeople.  We help our members connect with research mentors, and provide tutoring for academic success.  We also host fun chemistry events, such as various experiments and ACS educational programs. ACS at UCF also coordinates many volunteering opportunities for our members.  From running science experiments in the local community, to hosting booths for STEM day, to volunteering at the Orlando Science Center, we are always ready to help.  Our club prioritizes community outreach, and we have lots of opportunities for our members to volunteer. Interested in joining?  Visit  acsatucf.com  to see when our meeting times are for this semester or send us an email at president.acsucf@gmail.com. Meetings are held: Monday @5:00 PM in PSB 160 Our Current Officers: President:  Arianna Guemarez Vice-President:  Emilina Schmidt Secretary:  Myrah Bracero Treasurer:  Matthew Hiciano Event Coordinator:  Sobirjon Sharipov Outreach Coordinator: Malia Jeukeng

organizations.name: After The Sect

organizations.name: Pi Delta Psi Fraternity, Inc.
organizations.description: Pi Delta Psi Fraternity, Inc. is the first and only Asian-based fraternity at UCF. We seek to empower the UCF community and to help break down stereotypes of the Asian community while giving back as well. Our National Philanthropy is The Asia Foundation.

organizations.name: Multicultural Association of Pre-Health Students
organizations.description: Welcome to Multicultural Association of Pre-health Students!   Watch our introductory video: Click here   Since our commencement, we have flourished in aiding underrepresented students into professional schools through career specific meetings, shadowing opportunities, local medical school trips, community philanthropy, and annual attendance to the American Medical Educational Conference hosted by the S.N.M.A.   Who We Are: Multicultural Association of Pre-medical/health Students, or MAPS, represents the undergraduate and post-b accalaureate students of Student National Medical Association (SNMA). ( www.snma.org ) MAPS chapters are spread throughout the country at over 150 undergraduate institutions. They are well integrated into SNMA's infrastructure, participating in regional and national events. We, along with other chapters in Florida help constitute Region Four. Our organization's advisor is also an academic coordinator with the College of Health Sciences at UCF: Catherine Manz. Our Objective and Purpose: To provide underrepresented pre-med/health students with knowledge, skills, and experience that are both prerequisite and concomittant to professional participation in health care fields. To improve multicultural students matriculation into all professional health related programs, with an emphasis on medicine. Our group is open to all pre-med, dental, physical therapy, occupational therapy, physician assistant, athletic training, podiatry, optometry, psychology, nursing, and other allied health professions. ***United we aspire, together we Achieve*** Like us on Facebook at  https://www.facebook.com/mapsucf  Follow us on Instagram at   https://www.instagram.com/mapsatucf/  Visit our website at:  https://www.mapsatucf.org Check out our past events:  Click here

organizations.name: Phi Mu Alpha Sinfonia
organizations.description: Formed in 1898, Phi Mu Alpha Sinfonia is the world's oldest and largest secret national fraternal society in music. We bring together musically inclined individuals who share a passion for creating and performing music, fostering a sense of camaraderie and artistic growth, all while supporting our local community through the power of music.

organizations.name: MEDLIFE
organizations.description: MEDLIFE Orlando, founded in 2013, is a branch of the international non-profit organization MEDLIFE. MEDLIFE is a secular, vo lunteer-run global health organization whose mission is to help families achieve greater freedom from the constraints of poverty, empowering them to live healthier lives. Our patients did not choose to be poor, but they do choose to strive for a better life. MEDLIFE stands beside them in this pursuit. https://medlifeucf.wixsite.com/home

organizations.name: Women's Club Soccer @ UCF
organizations.description: Hello, welcome to Women's Club Soccer at UCF!! We currently have practice Monday/Tuesday/Thursday from 4:30pm-6:30pm on the RWC Grass Field. Please email wcsoccer.ucf@gmail.com or text 954-909-1362 before you come out for further details.

organizations.name: Women in Business UCF
organizations.description: Women in Business UCF was created support and empower the next generation of female business leaders by developing technical skills and a strong social network. Our main goal is to help all members obtain a job offer prior to or upon graduation. We are here to mentor and guide female college students by providing access to resources that will enable them to perform at executive levels in professional and educational environments. We will have educational meetings with businesswomen that have excelled in the workplace and will provide several social networking opportunities for members to build strong relationships and gain connections to big opportunities.  Gaining internships and job offers is incredibly important for student success upon graduation. It's no secret that men have been favored by employers in most business professions, notably finance, accounting, and investments, among others. There is a noticeable wage gap between males and females. Because of this, we see that women are still at a large disadvantage in professional environments. We aim to prepare female UCF students to help bridge the gap between businessmen and businesswomen that has existed for far too long.

organizations.name: College Democrats at UCF
organizations.description: College Democrats at UCF is the representation of the Democratic Party on the campus of the University of Central Florida. We strive to promote the ideals of equality, equity, dignity, justice, integrity, and progress that define the Democratic Party. We are committed to creating an environment where we can celebrate the accomplishments of the Democratic Party while also demanding more and keeping our party accountable to the voters who believe in it.  Our organization highlights progressive politics at the local, state, and federal level. We also invite lawmakers, local officials, candidates, and activists to come to General Body Meetings and special events. Our organization also has access to various internships, fellowships, and job opportunities! Keep Moving Forward ‚Äì it is a phrase so simple, yet defines us as an organization, and as a nation. It a phrase which tells us, that with every victory comes a new challenge, and with every challenge comes a new opportunity.  Be sure to follow @ucfdems on Instagram for updates!

organizations.description: TEA@UCF is an organization for UCF students of all years and majors who are interested in a career in the themed entertainment industry. Students will learn how to succeed in the field from industry experts through guest speaker events and tours at Orlando's most exciting themed entertainment destinations. organizations.description: 4EVER KNIGHTS (4EK) is an organization that serves as the bridge between students and UCF Alumni, hosting events, programs and campaigns to connect all Knights and create tradition in the process. organizations.name: Russian American Student Association
organizations.description: The Russian American Student Association at the University of Central Florida is a cultural organization with the goal of enriching the community with knowledge about the Russian culture and language. The club strives to show members and the community as a whole the richness of Russian culture by providing an opportunity to see, hear, and taste the culture. The club is open to everyone, not just native Russians. The Russian American Student Association hosts weekly meetings as well as larger cultural events ranging from musical concerts to ballet. Weekly meetings balance educational and social activities: movies, food, arts, and discussions are a glimpse of what the Russian Club members may experience on a weekly basis. Members of different ages and from different spheres of life are united by the common curiosity of Russian history and culture. The Russian American Student Association officers and members are determined to build cross-cultural bridges through learning. Sharing experiences of immersive cultural exploration lessens the divide between cultures and nations, which is what the club ultimately hopes to achieve.

Our goals include educating members on investment strategies and risk management, offering opportunities to apply theoretical knowledge in real-world settings, managing our student-run portfolio, hosting networking events with industry professionals, and encouraging collaboration and discussion on market trends and economic developments. FIRST MEETING: September 8th, 2:30-3:00pm, SU221 (Student Union) For Inquiries Email:  ucfinvestmentclub@gmail.com Join our Discord! https://discord.gg/z6MKJ3HVTv Check out linktree! https://linktr.ee/InvestmentClubAtUCF

Practices will held at the tennis courts near the UCF recreational center and are Monday and Wednesday 5-8pm and Saturdays 9-12 pm.

organizations.name: Best Buddies
organizations.description: Please contact us at UCFBestBuddies@gmail.com for questions regarding membership, upcoming events, or how to get involved!   Best Buddies International is a nonprofit organization dedicated to establishing a global volunteer movement that creates opportunities for one-to-one friendships, integrated employment, leadership development, inclusive living, and family support for individuals with intellectual and developmental disabilities (IDD).   The UCF chapter is a friendship chapter, focused on partnering up our members in one-to-one friendships. Pairs have the opportunity to hang out outside the club like any friends would, as well as attend our weekly socials and over 5 large-scale events, including the Talent Show, Hoedown, and annual Inclusion Week in the spring.    As a part of our mission towards inclusion, we partner with other organizations on campus. Some of our highlights include partnering with Greek life, UCF athletics, ACS, LMSA, CHAARG, Knights Exemplar, the UCF Police Department, Active Minds, and Special Olympics.   Everyone has room for one more friend!

organizations.name: ReliefShare @ UCF
organizations.description: Who are we?  ReliefShare @ UCF is a nonprofit organization that takes medical surplus from hospitals that donate it to us and send it to countries where this medical supplies could be used.   We also pack meals for places that are affected by food desserts or natural disasters.  This is the first chapter on a university campus. What is medical surplus? Medical surplus is any expired medical supplies or medical supplies that is unexpired and unused. Usually this expired medical supplies is in decent condition and can be used to an extent. The condition of medical supplies will be examined by the recipient. Unexpired medical supplies maybe be donated to us in the case that a Hospital changes the brand of supplies and must remove all of the previous brand's merchandise by discarding them.  What will we do at events? Our events will include sorting medical supplies into 10 categories based on the medical device's use (e.g Urology, Cardiology, Surgical). Then we would inventory each item into a spreadsheet using a program called Orcascan. The program allows us to scan a barcode or QR code on the device and automatically log it into a spreadsheet.
